title: banana cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler.
Add milk, slowly mixing.
Cook until thick.
Cook 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Stir small amount of mixture into the bowl with the egg yolks.
Pour the egg yolk mixture back in with the hot mixture while beating.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove; add butter and vanilla and cool.
Slice bananas into shell; cover with filling. Top with meringue.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly with hands.
Pinch off small portions and form into balls.
Place on cookie sheet close together.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until done.
Can be frozen and cooked as needed.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Let cream cheese sit until soft.
Mix other ingredients together.
Pour into graham pie crust.
Place in refrigerator about 1 hour before serving (longer if you like icebox pie).

title: marinated cheese and crackers
directions: Slice cheese blocks in half lengthwise. Then slice each of those halves into small 1 x 1-inch slices. Alternate Cheddar and cream cheese slices in a shallow pan. When finished, pour the Italian dressing over the top of the cheese and marinate overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: eggless, butterless, milkless cake - world war i
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, water, raisins, nutmeg and cinnamon together.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Cool and add baking soda, dissolved in a little water.

title: jean's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together saving a small dab tomato sauce to spread on top.
Add enough crumbled crackers to produce a stiff mixture and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Drain off excess grease before serving.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cover zucchini, onion and carrots with water and boil a few minutes; drain.
Mix together soup and sour cream; mix with vegetables.
(If using a 9 x 13-inch pan, prepare 2 packages stuffing mix with 1 cup margarine.)
Mix stuffing and margarine. Put one half of stuffing mixture in the bottom of a buttered casserole.
Add vegetable mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine all
ingredients
(except
coconut) in blender. Blend on low speed 3
minutes.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie dish. Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: icebox pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars, milk and marshmallows in top of double boiler.
Let cool.
Fold in 1/2 pint Cool Whip.
Pour in pie shell and chill.

title: oven bean bake
directions: Set overnight in cold water, lemon juice and vinegar; clean in the a.m.
Cook feet in cold water.
Put just over feet and season at this time.
Boil spaghetti (number 9 size).
Cook until done; set in cold water.
Take cooked pig feet out of water.
Put on side.
Put spaghetti in pig feet juice.
Add sauce to pig feet and spaghetti; if you wish add sliced green onions, not both.
Ready to serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Dough will be very stiff.
May blend by hand.
Do not chill!
Make 2 balls and roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cook on top rack of oven at 400° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately after taking from oven.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: spinach-onion dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Beat by hand.
Pour into pastry pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: austrian stuffed chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Finely chop the liver.
Set aside. Cut rolls into thin slices and pour the milk over them.
Set aside for 5 minutes.
Cream the 1/2 cup butter.
Add liver, egg, egg yolks, parsley and seasonings.
Combine butter mixture with the sliced rolls, mixing well.
Season chicken inside and out with salt and black pepper.
Spoon stuffing into chicken cavity.
Skewer shut.
Loosen skin of the breast with your fingers.
Insert 1 tablespoon butter in each breast.
Place chicken in a roasting pan. Pour in chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, basting occasionally with broth.
Add more water if necessary. Remove onto platter.
Carve and serve.
Good served with rice pilaf and a green salad.

title: crisp caramel clusters
directions: Combine oleo, caramels and milk; melt over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator in airtight containers.

title: mediterranean stroganoff
directions: Cook broccoli and carrots in boiling, salted water 5 minutes or until crisp and tender.
Drain.
Saute mushrooms, leek and garlic in butter until mushrooms are tender.
Blend in flour. Stir in cream, soy and bouillon.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add drained veggies, wine and olives.
In small bowl, combine sour cream, ricotta and Parmesan.
Gradually stir 1 cup hot mixture into cheese and then return to pan.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes until heated.
Do not boil!

title: bo's cookies
directions: Mix in order given, beating eggs and sugar with mixer.
Drop from tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheets and flatten.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
(Dough can be made into rolls, wrapped in waxed paper and frozen.)
Makes about 20 dozen.

title: mound balls
directions: Heat Karo syrup and almond flavoring until runny. Mix in coconut. Let cool completely. Shape into balls. Place on wax paper and refrigerate. Melt chocolate chips with small amount of paraffin wax. Dip coconut balls to coat. Place on wax paper until set.

title: crowd-pleasing tin roof
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup crumbs for topping.
Combine rest of crumbs with oleo.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut ice cream into 1-inch thick slices.
Lay on top of crumbs.
Spread ice cream with spatula to cover base.
Sprinkle peanuts over ice cream and freeze.

title: barbecued miniature meatballs
directions: Combine eggs, water and contents of pancake mix envelope.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add beef; mix lightly.
Shape small meatballs, using about 1 rounded teaspoonful for each.
Arrange in single layer on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, until done.

title: mom's cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into a saucepan.
Add water if necessary to make a full cup.
Heat to a boil.
In mixing bowl, dissolve Jell-O in boiled pineapple juice.
Add lemon juice and cranberry sauce.
Beat with a mixer for 1 minute.
Put in refrigerator until slightly formed, approximately 1 to 2 hours, then add the remaining ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: baked carrot squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch square baking pan with nonstick coating agent or use a nonstick pan.

title: hot sausage hogeys
directions: Cut link sausage into 3-inch long links and then cut about 3/4 through the long way (to make a flat piece).
Brown sausage. Place sausage in large electric frypan.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for several hours, stirring occasionally.

title: fruit juice smoothie
directions: Mix together in blender and blend to a smooth consistency.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Mix 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle nutmeg and cinnamon on the top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced tea
directions: Run red hots candy in blender until powdered; mix with all other ingredients.
Use 2 or 3 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of boiling water.

title: pumpkin bread spice cake
directions: Pour dry ingredients in bowl.
Add wet ingredients and mix. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: frozen pumpkin cookie pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; press into bottom and sides of pie pan.
Chill.

title: rotini and cheese
directions: Cut cheese in small pieces and pickle in small pieces.
Cut red onion in half.
Mix together.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Stir first four ingredients in melted butter.
Add mushroom soup.
Place in casserole and top with cheese and dried onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Optional:
May use potato chips in place of dried onion rings.

title: peanut butter brownie pizza
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions and spread onto a greased 12 inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15-20 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool completely on a wire rack.

title: glazed carrots au gratin
directions: Peel and slice carrots diagonally.
Cook in salted water until almost done, but crisp.
Drain.
Add melted margarine and sugar to carrots.
Simmer, turning carrots frequently to glaze.
Serves 6.

title: party dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy consistency.
Chop beef finely and add to cheese.
Chop gherkins finely and add to mixture.
Chop green onions and add.
Blend in mayo to form dip consistency.
Add garlic powder to taste.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Great with Ritz and chicken and biscuit crackers.

title: polka-dotted macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain and pour into ungreased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Stir soup, milk and Worcestershire sauce into macaroni.
Cut frankfurters crosswise into very thin slices and arrange on top of macaroni mixture. Bake uncovered 25 minutes at 375° or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: here's-to-your-health bread
directions: Mix flours and oats.
Combine 3 cups flour mixture, wheat germ, yeast and salt in large mixing bowl.
Add water, cottage cheese, molasses (or honey) and oil to flour mixture; beat until smooth, about 3 minutes on high speed of electric mixer.
Stir in raisins and enough more flour to make a soft dough.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Flatten 1 can of biscuits completely covering bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add scrambled eggs, sausage and 1/2 of cheese, distributing evenly.
Flatten second can of biscuits, completely covering mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Place cream cheese on a plate. You may leave it whole or spread to a layer. Mix together shrimp and sauce. Pour over cream cheese. Serve with crackers.

title: baked chicken in gravy
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, in 2-quart dish.
Drizzle melted butter over pieces.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Add soup by spoonfuls over chicken.
Bake approximately 20 more minutes.
Stir gravy before serving with chicken. Easy and delicious!

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix jello with 1/2 the water called for on package.
Poke holes in cake with handle end of wooden spoon or similar object.
Holes should be spaced approximately 1 1/2 to 2 inches apart.
Pour jello evenly over warm cake and cool.
Stir dry Dream Whip and pudding together.
Add milk called for in pudding only.
Mix with electric mixer until thickened and spread over top of cake.
Whip cream in a metal bowl, adding 1 teaspoon vanilla and sugar to taste.
Spread over pudding layer.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Drain grease.
Add minestrone soup, water, Ranch Style beans, Ro-Tel tomatoes and stewed tomatoes.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with a pan of cornbread.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large skillet, saute onions in butter until golden.
Add flour, stir until smooth.
Add water, Burgundy, bouillon cubes, browning sauce and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: mackinac island omelet
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Beat combined yolks, milk and salt until thick and lemon-colored.
Fold into egg whites.
Melt margarine in 10-inch ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat.
Add egg mixture; cook 3 minutes or until underside is golden brown.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Make a deep crease across center of top.
Place process cheese spread on half of omelet; continue baking until process cheese spread begins to melt.
Slip spatula underneath, tip skillet to loosen and gently fold in half.
Combine preserves and almonds; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Serve over omelet.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs and bread crumbs in bowl.
Set aside. Mix chili sauce, cranberry sauce and lemon juice together with brown sugar.
Heat to melt.
Pour sauce on bottom of long pan. Make small meatballs and place in sauce.
Cook about 30 minutes at 350° until meat is done.

title: mashed potato cake
directions: Sift together first 8 dry ingredients in a bowl.
Set aside. Beat together eggs, Crisco, chocolate, sour cream, potatoes and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and beat again.
Fold in chopped walnuts.
Pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. When cool, spread with cream cheese frosting.

title: coconut-black walnut cake
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Blend well and add coconut, nuts and coconut extract. Blend well and pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° approximately 65 minutes.
Five minutes before cake is done make following sauce.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Grease and flour a pie dish or pan well.
Add mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
May add coconut or fruit.

title: sour cream salmon loaf
directions: Measure the corn flakes and then crush into crumbs.
Drain off half of liquid from salmon.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in a loaf pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage creole
directions: Brown the sausage.
Remove sausage and pour off drippings.
In same skillet, mix remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Add sausage, heat.
Serve over hot rice.

title: diet lo-cal sour cream
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients and process at low speed until smooth.

title: pepper steak
directions: While rice is cooking, pound meat to 1/4-inch thick and cut to 1/2-inch wide strips.
Sprinkle meat with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
Using a large skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add garlic; cover and simmer.
Stir in onions and green peppers for five minutes more.
Blend in cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring until clear and thickened (about 2 minutes).
Add tomatoes and stir gently.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with portable mixer until well blended and smooth.
Rinse and drain canned shrimp; add to cream cheese mixture, chopping fine.
Mix well.
Add sour cream and mix.
Dip is better if made a few hours before serving so flavors can mix.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out water. Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and Ranch Valley with spinach.
Add seasoning salt.

title: blonde brownies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In large bowl, beat sugar, margarine, egg whites and vanilla until smooth.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients alternately with water. Stir in chips.
Spread in greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Serves 35.

title: pumpkin walnut cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pumpkin, vanilla, lemon peel and juice.
Resift flour with baking powder, salt and spice. Blend into butter mixture. Stir in walnuts. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheets 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add almond.
Pour into 9-inch pie dish, well buttered.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Remove and let stand for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Cut the cake into thin slices.
Using 1/2 the cake, line the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Prepare pudding with milk. Fold in the sour cream.
Spread 1/2 of the pudding mixture on the cake.
Spread 1/2 of the pie filling on the pudding.
Repeat the layers, ending with the pie filling.
Chill 4 to 5 hours.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Put 4 cups water in pot and bring to a boil.
Break up ground beef and drop into water.
Add onion, tomatoes, tomato sauce, bouillon cubes and spices.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add Veg-All and macaroni; cook until macaroni is done.
Add more water while cooking, if needed.

title: walk to school cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and form into 1-inch diameter balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: reese's peanut butter ice cream
directions: You will need 1 ice cream freezer.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook 1 (16 ounce) box rainbow rotini according to directions. Drain; do not rinse.
Mix with other ingredients while pasta is still hot.
Chill.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients very well.
Pour into greased 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chicken marengo
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: homemade biscuit mix
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
With a pastry blender, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Store in an airtight container. Will keep up to 6 weeks at room temperature.

title: ice cream cake roll
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and vanilla; mix well.
Grease a cookie sheet with sides.
Cut wax paper to fit bottom of pan; grease top of wax paper.
Place paper in pan and pour batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Turn out on a towel that has been dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll up jelly roll shape.
Let cool.
Unroll and cover with ice cream.
Roll cake back up and put in freezer to chill.
Then cover with whipped topping and return to freezer until ready to serve.
Garnish with fresh fruit, if desired.

title: sugar plums
directions: Combine the figs, apricots, raisins, nuts and orange in a food processor
(use
chopping
blade).	Cover
and
process until the fruit is
finely chopped and well mixed (or grind in a food grinder
fitted
with
finest
blade; mix well).
Shape tablespoonfuls of the
mixture
into
balls.
Roll in coconut. (To toast coconut, spread in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes or lightly brown, stirring often.)

title: hot buttered rum drink
directions: Batter:
Cream butter with sugar.
Mix in cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
To store, refrigerate in a covered dish.

title: honey banana bread
directions: Combine and sift dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl. In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except nuts. Beat until smooth.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts when well mixed.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: party time meat loaf
directions: Mix well by kneading with hands.
Pat into 4 two-inch steamer pans.
Pour over tops of meat 2 (No. 10) cans Ragu sauce.
Seal edges with sauce.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 100 to 125.

title: hot sauce for chicken wings
directions: Melt butter and mix all together. Pour over cooked chicken wings or can simmer chicken wings in mixture.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread coconut on bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. (A foil pan works good because the depth of a smaller pan causes cake to run over.)

Add nuts on top of coconut, then pour cake mix over that. Beat the cream cheese, powdered sugar, oleo and milk together. Drizzle over the cake mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until top springs back.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 375° oven 45 minutes.
Put in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: beef and potato bake
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Pat meat into 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone. Cut into pieces. Boil spaghetti; drain and rinse. Put spaghetti in chicken broth. Leave about 2 cups broth for cooking onions and celery; cook until tender. Mix everything together. Put in baking dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cook 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: tossed salad surprise
directions: In a small bowl, mix together cranberry juice, vinegar and oil. Cover and put in refrigerator.
In a large bowl, combine greens, mandarin oranges and cheese.
Pour salad dressing mix over greens. Add pecan pieces and toss to coat.

title: tex-mex won tons
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, green pepper, shredded cheese, ketchup, chili powder and ground cumin in skillet until done, then add refried beans.
Add 1 teaspoon of mixture to a won ton; fold like a diaper, wetting the corners.
Then in a skillet or Fry Daddy, deep fry won tons until golden brown.
Serve with your favorite salsa.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange tomato slices over sauerkraut.
Spread with Thousand Island dressing.
Top with corned beef and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Separate biscuits and arrange on top of casserole.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes longer or until biscuits are brown. Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients well and pour into 2 (8 or 9-inch) layer cake pans that have been well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: berry pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Let cool.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in boiling water.
Cook mixture about 2-3 minutes or until mixture becomes clear.
Remove and cool.
After mixture cools, add Jell-O and stir until mixed.
Pour berries into shell and pour mixture over berries.
Ready to eat or can be chilled.
Cool Whip to garnish.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans.
Form into a ball. Roll ball in pecans and refrigerate until firm.
Can be made into 1 large ball, 2 medium balls or many mini cheese balls.
Freezes well.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Drain grease.
Add spices and catsup and mix together.
Press around slices of iron skillet or casserole, leaving hole in center.
Pour corn in center of meat.
Make corn bread according to directions on box and pour over hamburger and corn.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Turn out on plate.
Slice and serve.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add shortening, vanilla and 1 cup sour milk.
Beat 2 minutes with mixer, or 150 strokes.
Add melted chocolate, eggs and 1/2 cup sour milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into two 8 or 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: angel food apricot dessert
directions: Cut angel food cake in squares. Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cook the apricot nectar, sugar and cornstarch until thick and clear, then spread over cubed cake when it has cooled.
Cool in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Yields 12 large servings.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Steam vegetables until crispy tender; remove from heat.
In separate bowl, combine onion, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Place vegetables in a baking dish and pour soup mixture over them. Sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Bake in 350° oven until heated through (approximately 20 to 30 minutes).

title: zucchini square cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in margarine.
Reserve 1/2 cup of dough mix; set aside.

title: chocolate layer bars
directions: In bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, water, oil and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda; add to creamed mix and mix well.
Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in a medium size saucepan in a small amount of broth and soy sauce until translucent, about 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ponche de pina
directions: Simmer sugar, water, cinnamon and cloves for about 30 minutes. Strain; removing cinnamon and cloves.
Add pineapple, orange and lemon juice.
Pour over ice or frozen pineapple juice cubes.
One gallon ginger ale may be added to serve additional guests or to give sparkly taste.

title: night before warm sticky buns
directions: Spray Bundt pan or one piece tube pan with cooking oil. Arrange the frozen roll pieces in pan.
Sprinkle with the pudding mix.
Also, sprinkle cinnamon and pecans over rolls.
Melt the margarine and brown sugar; pour over rolls.
Cover with a towel; set out on the counter overnight.

title: salvatine(long flat italian cookies)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add butter, sour cream and vanilla.
Add yeast to water and let dissolve.
Add to egg mixture.
Add flour and work in.
Roll up and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Roll dough into rectangular shape using granulated sugar on board instead of flour.
Roll a little thicker than pie crust.
Cut into strips and twist, put on cookie sheet in oven at 350° until very light brown. Will get very crisp.
Bake about 10 minutes.

title: ribbon jello salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package cherry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Divide in 1/2.
Add 3 tablespoons water to 1/2 and add 1/3 cup sour cream to other 1/2.
Pour the 1/2 with water in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let set until firm.
Then pour over that the mixture of jello and sour cream.
Chill until firm.
Do the same with the lime jello and pour on top of cherry jello, chilling until firm after each layer. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water.
Cut in bite size pieces. Cook wild rice and herbs in chicken broth.
Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs, together.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: french toastdallas, texas
directions: Beat eggs, add canned milk to make a smooth egg mixture, not too milky.
Dunk a slice of white bread in the mixture and then fry it in a hot skillet with oil already hot.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter in a bowl.
Beat egg and then add egg and milk to sugar mixture.
Mix flour, baking powder and cocoa. Add to mixture.
Add nuts, if desired.
Drop by spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw the broccoli in a colander under cold running water.
While the broccoli is thawing, combine the soup, mayonnaise, sour cream*, lemon juice, curry powder, salt and pepper in a mixing bowl.
Grease the baking dish, drain the broccoli well and spread the broccoli over the bottom.
Sprinkle 1/2 the cheese over the broccoli.
Drain the chicken and flake it evenly over the cheese.
Pour the sauce evenly over the chicken and top with the remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: cheese tortilla rolls
directions: Soften tortillas in hot oil. Pat excess grease off with paper towel. On each tortilla, put a little onion, cheese and olives; roll up. Use a toothpick to hold together. Put in pan. Repeat. Cover with sauce. Add cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets before boiling.
Drain. Place a layer of cooked cauliflower, a layer of sliced hard-boiled eggs, a layer of grated cheese.
Continue until all ingredients are used.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Pour white sauce over all. Place in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: nut roll
directions: Mix and roll in powdered sugar.
Freeze.

title: pork stir-fry
directions: Prepare marinade sauce in a shallow dish.
Reserve 2 Tbsp. of marinade sauce and add pork to remaining sauce, turn to coat. Cover dish and refrigerate for 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix in eggs, vanilla, bananas and pineapple by hand.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mixed vegetables
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil.
Cool.
Pour over vegetables. Pack vegetables in jars.
Makes 8 to 10 quarts.

title: mirliton casserole
directions: Peel and cut mirlitons in small cubes.
Cook 25 minutes with garlic, 1/2 of onions, bell peppers and celery.
Saute shrimp and meat with remainder of vegetables in 3 tablespoons oil.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add can of gravy.
Combine with mirliton mixture, chopped tomato and seasonings.
Cook 15 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: green tomato raspberry jam
directions: Combine green tomatoes and sugar in saucepan.
Boil 10 minutes. Add jello.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Pour into jars. Refrigerate or freeze.
Makes 4 1/2 pints.

title: four layer dessert
directions: First layer:
Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool well.

title: spice drop cake
directions: Cut spice drops in thirds.
Mix with raisins and nuts.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream together shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add egg and beat well until fluffy. Add flour mixture alternately with applesauce and hot water.
Stir in spice drops, raisins and nut meats.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or use smaller pans as desired.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or just until done.

title: chili
directions: Lightly fry onion, green pepper, zucchini and garlic in olive oil, then place in
pot
with kidney beans, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add chili
powder, cumin seed, oregano, parsley flakes, curry powder and
ground
pepper.
Fry
ground beef in olive oil, adding salt as needed.
Drain grease and place meat in pot.
Bring all to boil, then simmer at least 30 minutes.

title: colonial cranberry salad
directions: Combine 1 cup water, sugar and cranberries in a saucepan; bring just to boil.
Remove from heat; cover and let cool for 5 minutes.
Combine 1 cup boiling water and jello; stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water, cranberry mixture and lemon juice; chill until partially congealed.
Fold in remaining ingredients; chill until firm.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy; add beaten egg.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to cream mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in each flavoring.
Spoon into prepared Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/4 hours.
Cool.

title: mom's chocolate cake
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix first
five ingredients well.
Fold in blueberries. Pour in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool 30 minutes
and
remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Freezes well.

title: broccoli-cauliflower slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients. Refrigerate.
Best when made a day ahead of serving.

title: orange marmalade cookies
directions: Beat the oleo, add sugar and beat again.
Add the eggs and beat until fluffy.
Mix the flour, baking soda and salt together. Add to the above mixture, alternating with the orange marmalade.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable rice soup
directions: In an 8-quart saucepan, heat oil, garlic and onions over medium high heat.
Saute 5 to 6 minutes or until onions are clear. Add V-8 juice, water, bouillon cubes and vegetables.
Heat until soup comes to a boil.
Add rice and kidney beans.
Allow to heat through.
Remove from heat and serve.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: norma's salad dressingceres, california
directions: Combine olive oil, vinegar, lemon juice and mustard in blender until blended.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches, or 2 loaf pans, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches.
Mix all ingredients; beat 30 seconds;
Pour into pan(s).
Bake until wooden pick inserted into center comes out clean, 9-inch loaf, 65 to 70 minutes; cool slightly.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan; remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.
To store, wrap and refrigerate up to 1 week.

title: spaghetti loaf
directions: Boil spaghetti with garlic in salted water until tender. Remove garlic; drain spaghetti and rinse.
Melt cheese in milk. Add to eggs.
Add salt, parsley, onion and spaghetti; mix thoroughly.
Pour into buttered loaf pan.
Bake in oven (350°) for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: holiday broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in a small amount of boiling water until tender. Drain and place in 2-quart casserole. Cover with soup.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter and sugar; mix well. Stir in beaten egg, water, and vanilla. Roll into 3/4 inch balls; place on a cookie sheet. Flatten with a floured fork. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt butter in shallow pan.
Coat potatoes with butter, then flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° for an hour. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chicken casserole(microwave)
directions: Microwave broccoli 5 minutes on High in box on a plate (remove paper).
Put chicken and broccoli in layers in a baking dish.
Mix soup, milk, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spread mixture on top of chicken
and broccoli.
Put stuffing on top and pour melted butter over the stuffing mix.
Microwave for approximately 15 minutes at Medium-high or until heated through.

title: sweetened condensed milk substitute
directions: Mix well and blend until smooth.
Setting bowl in pan of hot water helps dissolve the sugar.
This mixture can be used instead of Eagle Brand milk.

title: cajun fried rice(handed down from generation to generation)
directions: Fry sausage in oil until lightly brown.
Add chopped onion; saute.
Add rice and other ingredients except eggs and fry until crisp.
Stir constantly.
Add eggs and stir until eggs are cooked. Serve as main dish.
Nothing else is needed to go with this except children like catsup on it.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add oil and vanilla; beat.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Blend.
Fold in zucchini and nuts. Bake in greased and floured loaf pans (2) at 350° for about 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: old-time bread pudding
directions: Place buttered toast, which has been cut into squares, in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle raisins over toast. Mix together eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, milk, boiling water, salt, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour over toast and raisins; sprinkle 4 teaspoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: onions au gratin
directions: Cook onions in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain in colander for about 30 minutes.
Arrange onions in buttered baking dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Mix soup and sauces; pour over cheese.
Top with croutons.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and store in quart jar in refrigerator.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and other ingredients.
Put rhubarb in shell and pour custard over.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 300° for 30 to 40 minutes until done.

title: three-way vegetable salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Heat vinegar, sugar and oil. Pour over vegetables.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, add milk, vanilla, sugar, salt, melted margarine and bread crumbs.
Put floured raisins on bottom of pan and pour mixture over the raisins.
Bake at 350° until firm.
Serve pudding with a real fruit sauce.

title: scrambled egg and ham spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions to barely tender stage; drain.
Place ham, peas and water in large skillet and simmer for 3 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti.
Pour eggs over mixture; cook on medium heat until eggs are done.

title: cheesy ham bake
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Add milk gradually to soup and blend well.
Combine all ingredients except bread cubes.
Toss bread cubes and butter.
Arrange around edge of pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Brown.
Put on cookie sheet or in an electric skillet at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: edible water colors (jello)
directions: You will need a bowl for mixing, spoon, paper and brushes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix well, except spaghetti sauce and cabbage. Remove core from cabbage. Place cabbage in boiling water until leaves are soft and pliable. Remove each leaf and cut back of center vein so leaves can be folded. Roll 2 tablespoons of meat mixture into cabbage leaf. Put in heavy pot and pour sauce over rolls.
Cover with tight lid and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti; then add butter and eggs.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread on ground chuck or sausage.
Pour over top the Ragu sauce and even out.
Top with slices of Mozzarella cheese.
Put in oven 20 minutes or until it is heated through at 350°.
May be made a day ahead if preferred.

title: tempura cooking(deep-frying)
directions: Batter:
Mix the dry ingredients.
Stir milk into beaten eggs. Pour into the dry ingredients and beat.
Let batter rest at room temperature for 1 hour before using.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Fry sausage, rinse, dry and cool.
Mix all vegetables together with mayonnaise and pickle juice, then add corn bread and sausage. Serve.

title: berry jam(makes 1 pint)
directions: Stir all ingredients in preserving kettle over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Increase heat and boil mixture rapidly, stirring often until jam thickens.
Quickly skim off foam and pour hot jam to 1/8-inch top of jar.
For storing longer than several weeks, process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Add bananas, vanilla and nuts, if desired. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Mix all soups together well.
Add rice and put in a 9 x 13 pan.
Lay chicken on top of rice and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: golden harvest apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Sprinkle with flour; set aside.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in small bowl. Layer apple slices alternately with sugar mixture in pie crust. Press down gently to eliminate air pockets.
Dot with marmalade and butter.
Roll out remaining half of dough to circle 1-inch larger than pie plate.
Place over apples.
Fold edges under; flute.
Cut slits or designs for steam to escape.
Brush top crust with milk. Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a loaf.
Place in deep baking dish or pan (9 x 12-inches).
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Pour off any excess grease.
Add topping and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Baste every 10 minutes for at least the last hour (very important).

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Stir butter and sugar into boiling water until dissolved. Cool to lukewarm.
Soak yeast in 1/4 c. lukewarm water.
Add yeast and egg to butter mixture.
Stir in flour and salt.
Cool, rise, and put on well greased sheet cake pan and press evenly. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: no sugar cookies
directions: Boil raisins, chopped dates and coconut, chopped apples and water together for 3 minutes.
Add vegetable shortening.
Cool this mixture, then add eggs, sweetener, vanilla, flour, soda and chopped nuts, if you wish.
Mix and refrigerate until well chilled.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate in an airtight container.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat well.
Add other ingredients. Serve with fresh fruit - apples, pears, strawberries, etc.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add evaporated milk, eggs and vanilla in saucepan.
Add whole milk to make amount of pudding needed.
Boil until thickens, stirring.
Layer with vanilla wafers and bananas.

title: orange-carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl; toss gently to coat.
Chill several hours.
Yield:
about 6 servings.

title: sinful salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple (with juice), strawberries, nuts and bananas.
Pour 1/2 mixture into a bowl and let jell until set.
Spread sour cream over set jello. Add remaining mixture and jell.

title: mom northeim's rice pudding
directions: Mix all together and cook a little on top of the stove to speed baking.
Bake at 325° for about one hour.

title: almond crescents
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat margarine, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour and salt; mix until well blended.
Stir in oats and almonds.
Using level measuring tablespoonfuls, shape dough into crescents.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet, 14 to 17 minutes, or until bottoms are light golden brown.
Remove to wire racks. Sift remaining sugar generously over warm cookies.
Cool completely.
Store tightly covered.

title: beef barbecue cups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Separate dough and press in bottom and sides of prepared pan, forming a 1/4-inch rim.
Spoon 1/4 cup meat mixture into each cup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute; remove from pans.
Serves 10.

title: southern peach pie
directions: Melt caramels and butter in double boiler, stirring until smooth.
Combine sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Gradually mix in caramel sauce and nuts.
Turn peach slices into unbaked pie shell and cover with caramel mixture.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Filling will firm as it cools.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.
This pie freezes nicely.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Put broccoli, onion and celery in a bowl. Cover and microwave for 10 minutes until tender. Once your broccoli is cooked, add to remaining ingredients, then add just enough milk so it is moist, then bake.

title: angel food shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, stir together confectioners sugar and flour; set aside.

title: cottage potato casserole
directions: Cook; cool, peel and dice potatoes.
Dice green pepper and onion.
Make bread into crumbs.
Melt cheese and butter together. Mix everything together except corn flakes.
Place in greased casserole dish and top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: hermits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat butter, sugar and eggs together until well blended.
Stir in coffee.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon together.
Blend into shortening mixture. Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 minutes or until cookies feel almost firm.
Cool.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Grind together shrimp, shallots, 1 onion, bread and garlic; mix well.
Add salt and pepper; stuff into pepper halves.
Brown the stuffed pepper halves in heated Wesson oil and remove.
Chop remaining onion very fine and saute in same oil.
Add tomato paste and cook, stirring constantly, unti brick color.
Add tomato sauce and 2 cans of water.
Blend together thoroughly; add pepper halves and simmer gently for at least 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over steaming rice.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: fried frogs' legs
directions: Wash legs, remove skin by turning it down and pulling it off like a glove.
Wash and dry.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Dip in egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Saute in butter about 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown on both sides.
Makes 6 servings.

title: turkey meatball stroganoff
directions: Make meatballs by combining the first 10 ingredients in a large bowl and mixing well with your hands.
Form 2-inch diameter meatballs and brown in a large nonstick skillet on medium-high, about 5 minutes.
After meatballs are browned on all sides, add chicken broth and simmer until they are cooked through with no pink in the middle, about 10 minutes.
Take out meatballs and put them in a warmed serving dish.
The broth left in the skillet should be reduced to about 1/2 to 1/3 volume.
With the heat on low, add the mushroom soup and mix well.
Without boiling or simmering, add the sour cream and the mushrooms and stir until smooth.
Put the meatballs back in the sauce and heat through if necessary.
Serve over 10 ounces of cooked egg noodles that have been lightly buttered and parsleyed.
Makes enough for 8 or you can freeze half to eat at a later date.
The recipe makes about 24 meatballs.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: In medium sauce pan, cook onion in hot margarine until tender but not brown.
Add corn, broccoli, carrots, and water.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in soup, milk, cheese, and pepper. Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese is melted and mixture is heated.
Yum-yum!

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken, celery, bay leaves and onion in water until tender.
Remove chicken from broth and cool.
Remove bay leaves and add carrots, noodles, salt and pepper.
Boil 10 minutes. Remove chicken from bone.
Add to soup and heat until boiling.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Heat together milk, mayo and cream cheese.
Put chokes in greased, oblong baking dish or pan and add thawed spinach, cheese, etc.
Spread over vegetables.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Remove cover and bake 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Boil chicken until tender.
Save broth.
Debone and cut up chicken.
Add soups to broth and bring to a boil.

title: china town chops
directions: In large skillet, brown pork chops, then set aside.
Brown rice with butter.
Stir in 2 cups hot water and mushrooms.
Add contents of vegetable sauce envelope.
Place chops on top of rice in skillet.
Sprinkle with soy sauce.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, then simmer 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Serves 4.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Beat sugar and cream cheese in a large bowl until fluffy and light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add melted chocolate, vanilla, cocoa and sour cream, beating constantly.
Add melted butter and blend well.
Pour into spring-form pan and bake on lower rack for 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until edges are completely set.
Center may not appear set but will firm as chilled.
Cool until warm on wire rack.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from pan.

title: sugar cookies(christmas)
directions: Cream the shortening.
Add sugar, milk, eggs and vanilla. Then mix flour, salt and baking powder. Add to mixture.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Then roll out dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut in desired shapes.
Place on cookie sheet.
Brush with milk. Sprinkle with sugar or top with nuts, red or green sugar or tiny colored candies, gumdrops, cherries or raisins.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs and beat one at a time. Dissolve soda in buttermilk, stirring well.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add 1 cup mini morsels, melted chocolate, chocolate syrup and vanilla, stirring just until blended.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Invert cake onto serving plate immediately; let cool completely.

title: honey barbecue chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together well. Dip chicken pieces into flour mixture. Bake for 45 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; mix.
Blend 10 to 15 seconds; stop and blend again 10 to 15 seconds.
Pour into jar with tight fitting lid.
This does not need to be refrigerated. If you do plan to refrigerate it, use corn or cotton seed oil as most other oils will thicken when chilled.

title: rink-tum-ditty
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Slice Velveeta and put in soup.
Mix. Bring to a boil.
Simmer.
Put in 1 beaten egg.
Stir fast and frequently.
Serve hot over crackers or let cool and use as a spread.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip together until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill 2 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pie filling squares
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Mix in dry ingredients. Place 3/4 of batter in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with pie filling and then the remainder of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german potato salad(low-fat)
directions: Pare and cook potatoes in boiling salted water to cover until tender, about 25 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cut beef after pouring boiling water over it.
Mix all of other ingredients.
Use large loaf of French bread (fat).
Cut off top and hollow out center and make croutons.
Brush croutons and inside of bread (both top and bottom) with melted butter and garlic.
Bake at 350° until light brown and crisp.
Pour in cheese mixture.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use croutons for dipping, then break loaf.

title: ratatouille
directions: Spray a Dutch oven with Pam.
Set pan over moderate heat.
When pan is hot, cook garlic and onion until translucent.
Add remaining ingredients after it comes to a boil.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Undercook slightly if you plan to freeze.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Two and one-half cups equals 165 calories, 7 grams protein and less than 1 gram fat.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain well. Arrange broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Add chicken over broccoli.
Mix together mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese in separate bowl.
Spread over chicken.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Add onion rings on top.
Serves 6-8.

title: scalloped chicken(lo-fat)
directions: Heat 1/4 cup water in a small skillet over low heat.
Add celery, scallions and parsley; cook 5 minutes.
Place dressing mix in medium mixing bowl.
Add vegetables and cooking liquid plus an additional 3 tablespoons water; mix lightly with a fork.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick vegetable spray.
Place dressing mixture in bottom of dish and set aside.

title: chocolate butterscotch bars
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat, stir in peanut butter.
Mix in rice cereal.
Press into 13x9 buttered pan.
Pour morsels over mixture and place in warm oven (low heat) for just a few minutes until you can spread the morsels into a creamy consistency over the cereal.
Needs to cool at room temperature before cutting into bars.

title: pbj muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder, then stir in peanut butter.
Pour milk and eggs
over and stir just until flour is moistened.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full, then top with preserves or Old Fruit.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: my favorite peach pie
directions: Slice peaches. Cook cornstarch, salt and cold water until sauce is thick and clear. Add lemon juice and almond extract. Add Jell-O and cool. Put sliced peaches in cooled sauce and mix well. Pour into baked pie crust and place in the refrigerator to set. When ready to serve, top with Cool Whip.

title: egg burrito(low-fat, low cholesterol)
directions: Spray nonstick skillet lightly and saute onion and bell pepper on low heat.
Whisk egg whites and food coloring; pour into skillet over onion and bell pepper.
As egg starts setting, sprinkle with cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add turkey if used.
When eggs are completely set, fold over.
Cut into four equal portions and place in steamed tortillas (place tortillas in between paper towels and cook for 30 seconds).
Roll and serve.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Add the drained vegetables and simmer 10 minutes.
Seal while hot.

title: pumpkin apple streusel muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients and set aside.

title: carrots and cranberries
directions: Combine apple, cranberries, carrots, sugar, salt and cider in buttered casserole.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 60 minutes, stirring once.
Yields 6 servings.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, if desired.
Slice potatoes crosswise into thin slices.
Melt margarine and dip each potato slice into melted margarine and layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Continue to layer until all potato slices are used.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender and cheese is bubbly.

title: turkey chowder
directions: In a 3 1/2-quart saucepan, combine turkey stock with potato, onion, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from heat; add celery soup.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients. Reheat gently.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Combine all ingredients.
Add pecans last. Use juice from pineapple to soften cheese if necessary.
Form ball and chill, overnight if possible.

title: daddy's vegetable dish
directions: Melt margarine in fry-pan.
Cook on low heat until vegetables are tender.

title: rock cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Add egg yolks and mix well. Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves; then add to creamed mixture.
Add walnuts and raisins.
Beat egg whites and add to mixture.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: In bowl, mix together apples, 1/2 to 1 cup sugar (amount will vary with sweetness of apples) and cinnamon.
Arrange in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: waffles
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together into a bowl.
Mix all wet ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add to flour mixture. Beat until well blended.
Adjust milk to reach consistency of heavy cream.
Pour into a preheated waffle iron until steaming stops.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients for filling and mix well.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until firm.

title: best pound cake
directions: Cream oil and butter.
Add sugar and cream until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder; add to mixture alternately with milk.
When well blended, add flavoring.

title: layered beef stew
directions: Layer in covered roasting pan in order given.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon until crisp. Drain.
Cool and crumble.
Pour out all but 2 tablespoons of the drippings and saute onion. Cut cheese into small pieces.
Combine corn, cheese, bacon, onion, beaten eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with a little more chili powder.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Melt 1 stick of oleo and mix with all but cheese and crackers. Put in a 13 x 9-inch greased dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Dot with last stick of oleo.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Delicious.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly and form into 2 rolls.
Chill, slice and bake in 350° oven.
Watch so don't burn.

title: stuffed zucchini squash
directions: Wash zucchini, cut off ends, do not pare.
Cook zucchini in boiling salted water 5 minutes.
Halve zucchini lengthwise, remove pulp with spoon.
Save shells.
Combine pulp with bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, onion, parsley, salt, pepper and eggs.
Mix well. Fill zucchini shells with this mixture. Dot with butter and sprinkle with additional Parmesan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: a cheese danish
directions: Unroll 1 can of rolls and press firmly in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Spread mixture over the rolls.
Unroll second can of rolls and place on top of mixture.
Brush top layer with beaten egg white.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Prepare glaze with 10x sugar and milk.
Spread on glaze.
Chill overnight.

title: grandma's bread pudding
directions: Mix together; dot generously with butter.
Sprinkle a little more cinnamon on top.
Bake in buttered Pyrex baking bowl at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold with whipped topping.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients and enjoy.

title: texas ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Combine cornflakes, oatmeal, flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed ingredients slowly.
Add coconut, vanilla and nuts.
Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together sugar, pumpkin, eggs, oil and vanilla; set aside. In a large bowl, mix flour, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and baking soda.
Add wet mixture to dry mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together twice.
Mix in bowl with remaining ingredients.
Mix 20 minutes.
Grease a tube pan and bake for 1 hour (check at 45 to 50 minutes).
Start in a cold oven set at 350°.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Melt margarine; add onion, celery and green pepper and saute. Combine all ingredients.
Shape into small cakes.
Place in refrigerator for an hour or so.
This will keep them from falling apart when fried.
Dip in flour and fry in oil until golden brown.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease inside of 10-inch ovenproof skillet and heat in oven for 3 minutes.
Tilt skillet to coat bottom with oil evenly.
Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Pour into hot skillet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 9 to 10 servings.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed in glass bowl.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator overnight.
Toss lightly with 1 pound bacon bits fried crisp just before serving.

title: corn relish(50 years old)
directions: Slice pork about 1/4 inch thick and parboil (put in a pan with a little water).
Cook 5 minutes and drain.
This will remove salt from pork.
Panfry or deep fry until browned.
Remove pan and drain (Poor Man's Steak).

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions; drain. Cover and keep warm.
Meanwhile, rinse chicken; pat dry.
Cut chicken into thin strips.
For sauce, combine undrained pineapple, cornstarch, hoisin sauce and ginger; set aside.

title: "uncle pete's" chicken liver pate
directions: Saute liver, onions and garlic in butter or margarine.
Cook until tender and slightly browned.
Remove crusts from bread and cube.
Add all ingredients to a food processor and blend; adding enough mayonnaise to hold together.

title: cheese bars
directions: Spray 7 x 11-inch pan with nonstick coating.
Layer Monterey Jack, Cheddar and chilies.
Combine eggs, flour and sour cream; pour over cheese and chilies.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let set for a few minutes before cutting into bars.
Serve hot or cold.

title: fluffer nutters
directions: Spread one slice of bread with butter and marshmallow cream. Spread other slice with peanut butter.
Put two slices together and enjoy.
Great with a cold glass of milk.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Remove thick/tough peeling from potatoes leaving as much tender peeling as possible.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices & set aside.
Cut bacon into 1/4-inch bits and saute in a large saucepan until lightly crisped. Remove bacon bits with a slotted spoon leaving the drippings.
Set bacon aside.
Add onions and celery to drippings and saute until tender but not browned.
Add broth, water, pepper, salt and parsley flakes and bring to a simmer.
Stir in diced potatoes and allow to simmer for about 5-10 minutes.
Begin adding instant potato flakes to thicken if desired, adding 1 tablespoon at a time until you have a fairly thick consistency.
Allow to simmer for a few minutes to have the potato flakes absorb to their maximum.
When the consistency that you wish is reached, slowly add the cream, stirring constantly.
Allow to heat through but not boil.
Add reserved bacon bits, stir and serve.

title: creole salad with celery seed dressing
directions: Toss lightly in a large bowl.
Pour celery seed dressing over salad, tossing again.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Yield:
6-8 servings.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients except wieners.
Roll wieners in batter and fry in hot oil until brown.

title: date cake
directions: Pour hot water over chopped dates; let cool.
Add soda when dates are cool.

title: christmas philly wreath
directions: Mix together and form a wreath shape on party plate.
Sprinkle about 1 teaspoon of parsley on top for decoration.
Chill overnight to get flavors to blend well.
Great on vegetables or crackers.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Heat the stock.
Add the broccoli, onion and bay leaf.
Simmer 1 hour.
Combine the flour and butter to make a roux.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Whip the roux into the stock until it is thickened and smooth.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Put the mixture through a food mill and add the hot milk and cream. Season with the salt and pepper.
Serve it hot with croutons.
Any vegetable can be used instead of broccoli.
Makes 12 (8 ounce) portions.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pack tightly in quart jars and seal.
Process 50 minutes in boiling water.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until whites are stiff but not dry.
Fold in yolks, cottage cheese and sugar substitute.
Do not over mix.
Place mixture on sheet, placing one tablespoon on top of another until each roll is about 2 inches high.
Repeat until you have six piles.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake 1 hour.
Yield:
6 rolls.
Carbohydrate 0 g, protein 8 g, fat 6 g, calories 86.
Two rolls = 1 meat exchange.

title: instant black forest pie
directions: Spread preserves over bottom of baked pie shell.
In mixing bowl, combine pudding mix, yogurt, creme de cacao and vanilla. Beat well with rotary beater.
Spread over preserves.
Cover and chill several hours.
Before serving, spread topping over filling. Sprinkle with chocolate.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, bell pepper and hot pepper; drain. Add tomatoes and tomato paste and sugar.
Let simmer for about 30 minutes.
Cook rice.

title: aunt susie frey's sugar cookies
directions: Refrigerate a few hours or overnight and bake.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Blend margarine, flour and chopped nuts well.
Press into prepared baking dish.
Bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: peanut butter 'n jelly bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in beaten eggs; stir until mixture is smooth.
Reserve 1/2 of mixture.
Press other 1/2 onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread grape jelly evenly over crust in pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup peanut butter chips over jelly.
Crumble remaining dough over chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven. Immediately sprinkle with remaining 1 cup of chips.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: apricot pork chops
directions: Drain apricots, saving 1/4 cup of syrup.
Cut apricots in half.
In skillet brown chops (use oil if necessary).
Pour off fat; stir in soup, sour cream, syrup and green onions.
Cover. Simmer 25 minutes or until done, stirring occasionally.
Add apricots and cook for 5 minutes more.
Serve with rice.
Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs well; add milk, salt and dry mustard.
Mix well; fold in sausage, cheese and bread.
Place in 8 x 10 baking dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma alexander's oatmeal cake
directions: Stir butter, oatmeal and boiling water together; let stand 20 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients together; add oatmeal mix and stir well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: creamy pasta with roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Snap off and discard tough ends of asparagus. Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Cut mushrooms in half (or quarters if large). Cut bell peppers into 1-inch squares. Combine vegetables in bowl; add olive oil and mix lightly. Press garlic over vegetables. Add salt and black pepper; mix well. Pour into baking pan. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: quick easy brownies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa together.
Add flavoring and eggs. Add melted butter, Karo and nuts.
Bake at 300° in 8 x 8 pan for 35 minutes.
Test for doneness.
These brownies will be chewy.

title: frosted creme cake
directions: Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Line bottom with waxed paper and generously grease again.
Mix together baking powder, salt and eggs in bowl, using an electric mixer on medium speed.
Beating constantly, add sugar, then Karo, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Mixture will be thick and light.
Fold in flour and vanilla.
Pour batter in prepared pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: peppers in tomato sauce
directions: Clean red, green and yellow peppers and dry well.
Cook tomatoes, rub through colander and remove seeds.
Cook into thick sauce.
Fry peppers in oil slowly until tender.
Add 4 or 5 hot peppers to about 1 average size sweet pepper in jar.
Pour boiling tomato sauce over peppers and seal.
Salt to taste.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Mix butter, sugar and salt.
Add vanilla, pecans and flour. Press half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread jam over top.
Crumble remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen grasshopper pie
directions: Crush cookies in blender or food processor.
Reserve some crumbs for garnish.
Mix together cookie crumbs and sugar.
Press into 9-inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Dip meat in eggs, then in 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Brown in oil or butter and set aside.
Saute 2 onions and 2 cloves garlic.
Add whole tomatoes, tomato sauce and spices. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer with lid on for 45 minutes.
Remove lid and simmer about 10 minutes longer.
Layer in casserole dish.
Layer sauce, cheese, meat, sauce, Mozzarella cheese and meat in casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly and brown on top.

title: chocolate sugar cookies
directions: Mix and
chill.
Roll in ball.	Dip in orange juice and then sugar and
flatten	with
fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Bring butter or margarine, sugar, milk and egg to a boil. Cook 1 minute. Then add remaining ingredients. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Line pan with whole graham crackers. Pour filling over graham crackers and spread evenly. Top with another layer of whole graham crackers. Spread on icing.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix 1 cup water with rice and 3 soups.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken on top.
Pour remaining water over chicken. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: spam casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Add sugar and melted butter.
Press mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Dream Whip according to package directions.
Beat in softened cream cheese.
Pour over crackers. Chill until firm (2 hours).
Pour pie filling on top. Refrigerate.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all together. Shape into loaf. Roll in crumbs on foil and wrap foil around, folding edges. Chill for several days.

title: fruit tea
directions: Steep tea for 15 minutes.
In one gallon pitcher, add 1 cup sugar and 6 ounces lemonade and tea.
Add enough water to make one gallon.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Wilt cabbage; drain.
Use a casserole dish, well-greased.
Layer ingredients, starting with beef, onions, cabbage and Spanish rice.
Then pour V-8 juice over layers and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Spread cheese on top and return to oven until melted.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Arrange on lettuce leaves. Top with dressing and sprinkle with paprika.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Keep refrigerated.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in muffin pans, if desired, in 300° oven until done.

title: shrimp and crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in butter, add Rotel, soups, and cool on low heat until smooth.
Add shrimp or crawfish and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: blueberry jello
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Stir until dissolved. Add pineapple, blueberry pie filling and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set until hard.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop all ingredients and add to following mixture:

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
Chill, then peel and grate into a large bowl.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, combine butter and cheese, stirring occasionally until almost melted.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes; stir lightly and turn into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken continental
directions: In
skillet,
brown
chicken with butter.
Cook rice as directed on box.
Once chicken is browned, add water, cream of chicken
soup and parsley.	Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir into rice and simmer 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: celery casserole
directions: Mix chestnuts, soup and celery.
Pour into baking dish.
Melt margarine.
Mix crushed crackers and almonds in melted margarine; spread on top of celery mixture.
Bake about 30 minutes at 325°.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Boil pineapple; add jello.
Cool.
Add cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Put into a 9 x 9-inch glass pan.

title: maple-glazed salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 475 degrees.
In small bowl, whisk maple syrup, soy sauce, ginger, cornstarch, and 1 Tbsp. water until blended.
In shallow 1 1/2 qt. casserole, place salmon skin side down.
Spoon glaze over fish and roast 15 minutes, without turning over, or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Baste once halfway through cooking time.
Sprinkle with green onion to serve.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Pre-heat oven to 400. Grease muffin pan or use paper liners. Beat together butter and sugar at medium speed until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in bananas until smooth. Mix together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Alternately stir flour mixture and buttermilk into egg mixture until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in nuts and vanilla. Do not overmix batter; it should not be completely smooth. Spoon batter into prepared pan, filling two-thirds full. Bake until lightly golden, 15 to 18 minutes. Serves 12.

title: jumbo amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop onto cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Mix egg, flour, milk and salt.
Separate onion into rings. Dip in batter, then deep fry until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Combine pie filling, water and sugar in saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O slowly and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple, Coke and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch dish and chill.

title: do-ahead noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles; drain well.
Brown chuck in skillet.
Remove from heat; pour off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Blend cottage cheese with cream cheese until smooth and creamy.

title: skillet trash
directions: Add all ingredients in large skillet.
Cook on medium heat, covered, until vegetables are tender.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine.
Add ground beef, brown and drain.
Add mushrooms and mushroom liquid, pepper, salt and flour.
Cook 5 minutes and add chicken soup.
Simmer 10 minutes and add sour cream.
Stir in minced parsley.
Serve over noodles.

title: blender cheese cake
directions: Crumb
graham
crackers;
combine
with
oleo and press into bottom
of	7
x
11-inch
pan.
Pour boiling water into blender container.	Add
gelatin and process in blender until gelatin is dissolved.	Add
lemon
juice and 1 cup of cottage cheese; process until smooth.
Repeat until all blended.
Pour into large
mixer bowl and add Cool Whip.
Blend well and pour over
graham
cracker crust.
Chill until firm.	Top with pie filling if desired.

title: banana pudding
directions: Stir box of pudding and milk until thick.
Stir in condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add pineapple last.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Top with additional Cool Whip.

title: cabbage casserole(microwave or conventional oven)
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion; drain.
Add tomatoes and rice; bring to a good boil, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cabbage, and remove from heat. In an 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan, layer cabbage and spread beef mixture over top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 15 minutes.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Brown bacon in a cast-iron skillet. Leave 2 teaspoons of bacon grease in skillet and put it in the oven as it preheats.
Mix eggs, buttermilk and cornmeal to form a thin batter.
Add baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Pour batter into hot skillet.
Return skillet to oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes until cornbread begins to brown on top.
Turn out of the loaf by inverting the skillet over a large plate and serve hot.

title: german cherry cake
directions: Soften butter.
Mix butter with eggs; beat in sugar, then flour.
Add baking powder.
Mix.
Pour mixture into greased and floured cake pan.
Dot the top with cherries.
They will sink in while baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown around edges.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix together, form balls.
Brown in skillet or if lazy, drop balls in spaghetti sauce and simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: peas
directions: Cook peas as directed on bag using bay leaf.
Drain.
Melt butter in peas.
Mix in soup and mushrooms.
Heat well.
May be served in pastry shells.

title: popcorn balls
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine first 6 ingredients; cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to brittle ball in cold water.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and if desired, color.
Pour immediately over warm popcorn.
Shape into balls.
Dip palm in water before shaping into balls as it will keep it from sticking to your hands.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: goldie reckard's joe froggers
directions: In large bowl, cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
In small bowl, mix together salt, water and rum and set aside.
In another small bowl, mix together soda and molasses and set aside.
Sift together flour and spices.
Add flour mixture alternately with liquids to cream mixture, beating well after each addition.

title: egg and ham casserole
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Butter 8 slices.
Put buttered side down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add ham and shredded cheese. Butter the remaining 8 slices.
Place buttered side down on top of ham and cheese.

title: potato salad
directions: Taste to see if it needs anything and add if it does.
Pour in bowl.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Serve.

title: one christmas pitta(an italian pastry made in calabria, italy)
directions: Make a pile of flour; make a well in flour.
Add eggs, salt, Crisco and yeast.
Mix with hands.
Roll into circle like pie crust; brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with sugar, raisins, nuts, cloves and some honey.
Cut in 2-inch wide strips.
Fold in half each strip lengthwise and roll into rosette.
Tie rosettes with thread.
Arrange together closely forming a circle and tie together.
Brush top with small amount of vegetable oil.
Line cookie sheet with brown paper bag.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.
Spread with honey while hot.
(Freezes well.)

title: farmer's delight
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in large casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy zucchini
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in butter in skillet until tender. Stir in onion salt, oregano and tomato sauce.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices together three times.

title: low-fat pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and yogurt.
Add ice water, one drop at a time, until dough is easy to handle.
Divide dough in half.
Roll 1/8 inch thick on floured board, being careful not to add too much flour (that makes dough tough).
Low-fat crust has 1 g fat in two pie crusts.

title: oyster dressing(custard type with eggs)
directions: Tear bread into 1/2 dollar size pieces.
Let dry overnight. Dissolve cubes in water.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: seven minute double boiler frosting
directions: Combine sugar, egg whites, corn syrup and salt in top of large double boiler; add cold water and beat on low speed of electric mixer for 30 seconds or until well blended.
Place over boiling water, beating constantly on high speed about 7 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and beat 2 minutes or until frosting is thick enough to spread.
Yields enough for 3 layer cake.

title: prewash(household hints)
directions: Gently combine water, ammonia and dishwashing liquid.
Pour into a well labeled spray container.

title: white chocolate macadamian nut cookies
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugars, beating well. Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt. Gradually add to butter mixture, beating well.
Stir in white chocolate and nuts.

title: pepper corn
directions: Shuck corn and clean up.
Cut corn off cobs.
Melt margarine in an iron skillet to bubbly.
Add corn to skillet.
Cook on high, then turn down and cover, stirring often. Add chopped peppers when corn is near done.
Add peppers according to your taste for hot.

title: chicken a la karen
directions: Blend melted margarine with stuffing and spread half in greased baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients except almonds; pour over stuffing mix.
Top with other half of stuffing. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
tags: Stove Top San Francisco stuffing mix

title: decorator icing
directions: Beat Crisco
5 to 10 minutes at high speed.
Add sugar, 1 cup at	a
time.
Add
flavorings and milk last.
Mix until smooth.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
