directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
Beat at medium speed the butter, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
At low speed, mix in milk and vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture, mixing well.
Refrigerate several hours.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick and cut with cookie cutters. Place 1 inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° approximately 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Mix in flour and salt.
Add milk slowly, continually stirring over medium heat until sauce starts to boil.
Lower heat and cook until thickened.
Add mustard and cheese.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Mix in cooked macaroni.

title: southwestern chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, salsa, black beans, and corn.
Add chili powder and black pepper.
Allow to sit for several hours.
Serve over mixed greens.
Top with monterey jack cheese.
If you have tortilla chips, serve with those.
If you have flour tortillas, cook in a very hot skillet with a little olive oil and cut into wedges to accompany the chicken salad.

title: tarragon chicken casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine soup, cream, tarragon and pepper.
Stir in the noodles and chicken.
Transfer to an ungreased 4-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese and paprika.

title: bambini
directions: Combine cheeses in small bowl.
Halve each biscuit, forming 20 thin biscuits.
Shape each biscuit half in 2 1/4 x 4-inch oval. Place a slice of pepperoni on dough and top with 1 tablespoon cheese mixture.
Moisten edges and fold dough over to enclose filling.
Pinch to seal.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: easy baked turkey
directions: Baste turkey with oleo, wrap tightly in foil.
Place in covered roaster pan.
Bake at 475° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn oven off.
Do not open oven door for 8 hours.
Turkey will be done and extra juicy.
This will not work if oven door is opened.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Grease glass container, approximately 10 x 10-inch.
Place cut rhubarb in pan.
Sprinkle with sugar, then sprinkle with strawberry gelatin.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix.
Gently pour water over all.
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake at 350° approximately 55 minutes.
Serve topped with whipped topping or vanilla ice cream.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together; store in jar.
Put 2 teaspoons in cup, pour boiling water over and stir.

title: butterscotch pecan pie
directions: Melt butter; add morsels and heat until morsels melt.
Remove from heat and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry flummery
directions: Cook berries with sugar and lemon juice for 5 minutes.
Butter bread.
In a loaf pan, alternate layers of buttered bread and blueberries.
Start with the bread and end with a layer of fruit. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Chill.
Slice and serve with table cream or whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate, milk and sugar.
Cool.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites (beat egg whites with 1 teaspoon cream of tartar for stiffer egg whites).
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill for at least 4 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Crumble together and spread over pumpkin mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool, then refrigerate.
Cut into squares. Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Drain and pull chicken into small pieces.
As soon as the pasta is cooked and drained, stir in cheese.
Add rest of ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crackers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain pears. Use 1 cup pear juice with 1 package lime jello. Bring to a boil, then cool. Blend 1/4 cup pear juice with the milk and cream cheese until creamy. Add mashed pears and jello mixture. Fold in the Dream Whip or Cool Whip.

title: honey chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces. Works best if slightly frozen. Mix honey and egg white in small bowl. Crush corn flakes really fine and place on a plate or in
small bowl. You will need to judge how much you prefer. First dip chicken into honey mixture, then roll into corn flakes. Place on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Melt butter; cream with sugar in large bowl.
Add beaten eggs; add dissolved yeast to mixture.
Add flour and stir until well mixed.
Place in airtight bowl and keep in refrigerator.
Drop by spoonfuls in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Can keep in refrigerator for a few days.
Use as needed.

title: poached winter fruit
directions: Place all ingredients in a non-aluminum saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Lower heat to medium.
Cover pan and simmer fruit until pears are soft, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and let sit at room temperature while you prepare the rest.

title: icebox cake
directions: Place a layer of biscuits in a baking tray, approximately 9 x 13-inches.
Top with a layer of applesauce.
Add another layer of biscuits and applesauce; end with biscuits.
Place in refrigerator for approximately 3 hours.
After 3 hours, remove from refrigerator.

title: oreo's delight
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and add butter.
Mix well crushed cookies and butter and place in bottom of pan for crust.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix well Philadelphia cream cheese and powdered sugar, then mix vanilla, pudding and milk together with cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over Oreo crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: vinaigrette (basic)
directions: Put mustard in the bottom of a salad bowl.
Stir the first 5 ingredients, whisking constantly.
Add vegetable oil and olive oil in a very thin stream.
Makes 6 tablespoons of vinaigrette, enough for 10 to 12 cups of salad greens.
Use shortly after it is made. Add whatever you like, garlic, anchovies, shallots, sliced mushrooms, chopped capers, etc.
May be used on grilled fish or cold roast beef (add horseradish) or chicken.

title: clara's chocolate pudding
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa and hot water for five minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cream butter and powdered sugar and add boiled mixture. Add marshmallows, nuts and egg whites.
Crush graham crackers and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture on top of this.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Stir in oats, coconut and chocolate chips.
Form into rolls on wax paper.
Freeze rolls before slicing.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well. Remove crust from bread and cube. Place bread cubes on the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan. Layer the sausage over the bread. Top with cheese. Set aside. In a bowl, beat eggs. Add milk, salt and mustard. Mix well. Pour egg mixture over layers. Let stand overnight in the refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Ham, bacon or sausage can be added.

title: no can relish
directions: Chop all vegetables really fine in a blender.
Mix them together in a large container.
Drain any excess water off.
Add 1/2 cup canning salt and let set for 2 hours.
Drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over mixture, mixing well.
Put in a gallon jar and put a white cloth over top of jar.
Will keep well in refrigerator for 1 year.

title: crescent chicken rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except rolls.
Put 1 tablespoon of mixture into each roll.
Roll up and place on cookie sheet.
Brush with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Cut up chicken into eighths.
Combine all the sauce ingredients and marinate chicken pieces for 1/2 hour, turning occasionally.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower or broccoli for 5 or 6 minutes until just tender; drain well.
Mix together the remaining ingredients. Butter 2-quart casserole.
Put some sauce mixture on bottom; layer with cauliflower or broccoli and sauce, ending with sauce on top. Sprinkle top with Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chinese clusters
directions: In heavy skillet, melt butterscotch.
Stir constantly over low heat.
Stir in noodles and nuts.
Mix to coat evenly.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Makes 15 to 20 cookies.

title: lucy's meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Place in baking dish and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into deep 9-inch pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Mix gelatin in hot water until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and dissolve, then add marshmallows and dissolve.
Finally, add crushed pineapple and put in refrigerator; chill.

title: no sugar cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes on low heat.
Add margarine, cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni & cheese casserole
directions: Combine cooked macaroni, salt, Velveeta, half and half, parmesan cheese and eggs.
Place mixture in a buttered casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees or until top is brown.

title: lemony kiss cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat margarine, sugar and lemon extract until light and fluffy.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Gradually add flour and almonds; mix well.
Cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate at least an hour for easier handling.

title: ultimate chocolate cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first seven ingredients; mix well. Stir in chocolate chips. Coat a 10 inch fluted tube pan with nonstick cooking spray and dust with flour; add batter. Bake at 350° for 45 - 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan to wire rack to cool completely. Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: chentilly cream
directions: In chilled bowl, whip cream until stiff.
Fold in sour cream, then sugar and vanilla.
Serve over fresh fruit.

title: easy au gratin potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes, mix with onions and soup.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly hot.

title: strawberry angel trifle
directions: Tear half of angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Place pieces into bottom of 3-quart glass bowl.
In bowl, combine pie filling and whipped topping.
Drizzle cake pieces with 1/4 cup fruit spread.
Then spread half of filling mixture over cake pieces.
Layer half of the pineapple, kiwi and strawberries over filling mixture.
Tear remaining cake into bite size pieces and place over filling.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Put butter, brown sugar, water and raisins, nuts or apples in a large 10 x 13-inch pan and melt.
Spread out rolls into big squares.
Spread with a mixture of 3 tablespoons butter, 1/4 cup white sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Roll up each square jelly roll style.
Cut into 1/4.
Place in raisin syrup.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn out onto serving plate so juice goes through buns.

title: ham-basil quiche
directions: Prebake pie shell for 5 minutes at 400°.
Mix ham, cheese and basil leaves.
Spread mustard on bottom of prebaked pie shell. Sprinkle with ham-cheese mixture.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 muffin cups or use paper baking cups.
Combine pancake mix, oats, sugar and cinnamon.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix only until moistened.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix beef and macaroni.
Add soups, pizza sauce and spices. Add 1 cup of the cheese and mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Add the rest of the cheese on top and bake 15 more minutes, uncovered.

title: fudge cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda,

baking powder, and salt; set aside. Cream shortening, add sugar gradually, beating thoroughly after each addition. Add vanilla, then well beaten eggs; beat until light and fluffy. Beat in flour mixture alternating with milk. Mix cocoa and hot water to form a smooth paste; beat into batter. Pour into greased and floured pans (3 - 8 inch or 2 - 9 inch) and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Bring first 4 items to boil over medium heat.
Don't mistake air bubbles for boiling.
Boil slowly for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Put on foil-covered cookie sheet.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix picante sauce and sour cream for sauce topping.
Mix cream cheese, chicken, tomatoes, green pepper, onion and sliced olives together.
Roll chicken mixture into tortilla shells.
Place sauce on top.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Then add cheese to top.
Bake for another 10 minutes.

title: quick hamburger casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown meat until lightly browned.
Add salt. Add drained beans and soup; pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Make instant mashed potatoes and spoon in mounds over casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: creamy ham and cheese noodles
directions: Saute celery, onion and green pepper in margarine.
Add milk and cream cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Add meat, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and salt; mix well.
Combine sauce and noodles; pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Make pastry, mix sugar, flour, and cinnamon.
Stir in blueberries.
Turn into pastry - lined pie plate; sprinkle w/ lemon juice and dot w/ margarine, cover w/ top crust and bake.

title: a different creamed corn
directions: Cook corn in cream in saucepan until heated thoroughly. Stir in salt, sugar and m.s.g.
Melt 2 teaspoons oil in small saucepan. Add
flour,
mixing
well.
Stir into corn mixture. Cook
until slightly
thick, stirring frequently.
Spoon into casserole. Sprinkle
Parmesan	cheese	over
top,
dot
with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix and make meat balls.
Brown in 2 tablespoons fat.
Place in casserole and make a gravy of drippings, flour, mustard, catsup and add enough milk to make gravy consistency.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a covered dish.

title: dried fruit cordial
directions: Mix wine, brandy and sugar in glass or ceramic container, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add the dried fruit and cover tightly.
Store in a cool, dry place for at least a month, preferably longer.
Dried fruit will swell in the liquid, so widemouthed containers are necessary.
Strain off the cordial and reserve the fruit for topping.
Or you can give the combination of fruit and cordial together as a gift.
This recipe is adaptable to any dried fruit, so don't be afraid to experiment.
(Even prunes make a delicious cordial, but you may want to call it plum liqueur.)

title: oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Fold in cocoa and rolled oats.
Drop from spoon onto wax paper.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash sweet potato and mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Mix 1 egg and 1/2 cup sugar and beat well.
Pour over pie and bake again until sugar is crisp.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Blend two minutes with mixer your cake mix, vanilla instant pudding, butter, eggs, water, oil and vanilla.
Put 1/2 of batter in tube pan.
Mix cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle over the batter. Pour in the remaining batter and bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple crisp coffee cake
directions: Measure corn flakes and crush to measure to 3/4 cup.
Set aside.
Measure 2 tablespoons margarine, sugar, the cinnamon and nutmeg into small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Add crushed cereal and mix well.
Set aside for topping.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken, remove and drain.
Cut into bite-size pieces. Mix all other ingredients, except biscuits, in a saucepan to a low boil.
Stir in chicken.
Bake biscuits.
To serve, pour into casserole dish and place biscuits on top or half biscuits and pour mixture over top.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream peanut butter and sugar.
Add the egg and vanilla;
beat until blended.
Roll 1 1/4 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 - 12 minutes or until tops are slightly cracked.
Immediately press one chocolate kiss into the center of each cookie.
Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks.

title: smoked pork chops
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan, place oil and pork chops.
Cover with thinly sliced potatoes.
Mix salt, pepper, garlic and tomatoes. Pour over potatoes and pork chops. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from oven; put pork chops on top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: easy jello
directions: Bring orange juice to a boil; pour over Jell-O to dissolve. Stir in buttermilk.
Kids will love this and it makes a pretty color.
Any flavor of Jell-O can be used.

title: lo-fat banana bread
directions: Total Fat Per Serving: 3.6.

title: date cake
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over these ingredients and mix well. Add 1 1/3 cups flour.
Stir in an 8 x 11-inch pan or 9 x 13-inch pan, but makes a thinner cake.
I like brown sugar frosting or can use the following as an icing.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Put ingredients in blender and blend well.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Add mayonnaise and mix well.
Great on wheat crackers.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Combine 1/2 cup cheese and bacon; mix well.
In a 2 1/2-quart bowl, layer spinach, cheese mixture, mushrooms, onions and peas. Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar; mix well.
Spread over salad to seal.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons cheese over top.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Serves 8.

title: mexican salad dip
directions: Place bean dip in center of large platter.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning; layer on top of bean dip; then add guacamole or avocado dip.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and black olives.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, sausage, cracker crumbs, onion, garlic and egg.
Mix salt and oregano into tomato sauce, reserving 1/4 teaspoon of oregano.
Set aside 1/3 cup seasoned tomato sauce and add remainder to meat mixture.
Form into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour remaining sauce over top and sprinkle with cheese and 1 1/4 teaspoon of oregano.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and tear into pretty small pieces.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth. Mix spaghetti mix, cream of mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Add chicken and spaghetti.
Put in casserole dish, uncovered.
Cover top with Velveeta cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: beef 'n' rice supper
directions: Heat large, heavy skillet.
Add beef and onion and cook, stirring constantly, until beef is browned and onion is tender. Stir in green pepper, salt, oregano, tomatoes, beef broth and rice.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer, stirring once or twice, about 25 minutes or until liquid is almost absorbed and rice is tender.
Remove to serving dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: chicken "spareribs"
directions: In skillet, heat oil and brown chicken on all sides, turning, about 5 minutes on each side.
In large bowl combine all other ingredients but cornstarch mixture.
Add to chicken and bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water now and add to chicken, stirring until sauce is thick and chicken is glazed.
Top with scallions.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and cornstarch.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour over prepared beets in saucepan; add butter and let stand 30 minutes.
If necessary, warm before serving.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Blend together in mixer salad oil, sugar and eggs.
Next combine in order given apples (cored, pared and cut in chunks), chopped nuts, salt, soda, cinnamon, vanilla and all-purpose flour. Combine all ingredients to make batter which will be stiff.
Spoon into a Bundt cake pan.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Mix sugar, cocoa, oil, eggs and vanilla together until well blended.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Will be moist.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Beat eggs in one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, mixing well after each addition.
Mix soda, boiling water and flavorings.
Pour in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes without opening oven.

title: rack of lamb
directions: Cut lamb chops into pieces.
Chop and place in bowl.
Mix peeled and mashed garlic cloves, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Rub onto meat.
On top of stove in big nonstick pan, put olive oil and saute meat on both sides on high.
Heat until brown, then place in oven at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: chili(good)
directions: On medium-high heat, brown meat in large pot.
Drain and rinse to remove fat.
Meanwhile, chop onion.
Add onion to meat and stir under onions until tender.
Add remaining ingredients to pot and let the chili come to a boil.
Turn down heat.
Cover and let the chili simmer for 20 minutes.
Can also be frozen and reheated.
Makes 8 (1-cup) servings.

title: dessert
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler; then mix in beaten yolks.
Let cool a few minutes.
Fold in stiffly beaten whites and whipped cream.
Add walnuts.
Put over broken angel food cake.

title: punch
directions: Combine sugar, cherry juice, lemon juice and pineapple juice. Mix well; add food coloring to desired shade.
Chill.
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.

title: stir-fry beef and broccoli
directions: Cut beef into narrow strips.
Cut broccoli into 1-inch pieces at a diagonal angle.
Cut onion into narrow wedges and separate. Combine beef broth, cornstarch and soy sauce in a cup.
Heat oil in a wok until very hot.
Add beef.
Stir-fry until brown.
Add soy sauce mixture to vegetables; add beef and cook.
Cover for 2 minutes.
Cook until sauce thickens.

title: classic sour cream cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl, combine cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth. Beat in eggs, then sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Cool.
Chill. Top with filling.

title: christmas pinwheels
directions: Put olives, chilies and pimento on paper towel to dry off. Mix cream cheese and dressing together.
Spread on 4 tortillas. Sprinkle olives, chilies, pimento and onions, then roll.
Chill for 2 hours, then cut.

title: fettuccine primavera
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook broccoli, zucchini, pepper, onion and basil in butter spread until tender. Stir in tomatoes and mushrooms.
Toss vegetable mixture with hot fettuccine.
Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
(Other pasta may be substituted.)

title: bread
directions: Warm water should be 105° to 115° or feel warm to inside of arm.
Pour warm water into a warm bowl; sprinkle in yeast.
Stir to blend.
In a large mixing bowl, blend sugar, shortening, salt and scalded milk until shortening is melted.
Add cold water to cool mixture to lukewarm.
Stir in yeast.
Add flour gradually. Turn dough onto floured surface and knead 8 to 10 minutes, sprinkling in more flour as needed to avoid stickiness.
Turn in greased bowl.
Cover with damp towel and let rise 2 hours until doubled (when touching dough it leaves an impression).
Punch down; turn over in bowl and let rise again 30 minutes.
Separate dough into 4 sections.
Roll out in rectangles (12 x 9-inch) and, folding under ends, fit into loaf pans.
Let rise in pans 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 40 or 50 minutes until tops are golden brown and knocking on top of loaf sounds hollow.
Brush baked loaves immediately with a little butter.
You can freeze loaves as soon as they're cool.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: sausage stuffed burger loaf
directions: In skillet, cook sausage with green pepper and onion until meat is brown and vegetables are tender. Drain off fat.
Blend in sauce mix and add 1/2 cup milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Stir in mushrooms.
Set aside to cool.

title: red lobster cheddar bay biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls onto an un-greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 - 10 minutes until golden brown.
Mix butter with garlic. Brush over hot biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.

title: egg noodles
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll out as thin as you want.
Let stand for 20 minutes and cut into strips.
Drop in boiling broth for 10 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip and put into cooled crust.
Slice bananas over the top.
Combine blueberries, water, sugar and lemon juice; thicken with cornstarch and let cool. Put on top of pie.

title: veggie tuna dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill 3 hours or overnight.
Stir before serving.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: quickie fudge(microwave)
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish; pour in milk. Put butter on top.
Cook for 2 minutes.
(Take out and stir enough to mix.)
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until blended good.
Freeze 20 minutes.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: steak-n-gravy
directions: Place cubed steak in baking pan.
Spread soup over steak. Cover pan with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frosting
directions: Combine flour and milk in saucepan.
Cook over low heat to medium sauce stage, cool.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix together and bake 1 hour in a 325° oven uncovered.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix all the ingredients except Tostitos and cheese.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan put partially crushed Tostitos.
Pour sauce over them. Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sirloin tip
directions: Cut and slice in strips.
Add all ingredients and put in crock-pot.
Cook several hours (start out at high heat for 2 1/2 hours and turn back to low for another 4 hours or until done). Serve with cooked noodles.

title: talarima
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon custard pudding cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Beat egg yolks.
Add to mixing bowl along with milk and lemon peel.
Mix well.
Add lemon juice.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, slowly adding remaining 1/2 cup sugar while beating.
Fold into batter.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Place in a shallow pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until slightly browned.
Serve warm or chilled with 10x sugar dusted on top.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and celery in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain off pan drippings; stir in soup and thyme.
Spoon meat mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart shallow casserole.
Spread potatoes evenly over meat mixture.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in melted margarine.
Mix together with remainder of ingredients except bread crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole. Bake 1 hour at 350°, stirring once halfway through baking and adding cracker crumbs for the last 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Soak the marshmallows in whipping cream for 6 hours.
Whip the cream and marshmallows together until stiff. Cut cake in half with thread or sharp knife to make two layers.

title: scorzette candite(candied peel)
directions: Boil each rind separately in water to cover generously for 2 minutes.
Drain and let dry.
Cut rinds into thin strips; weigh them and weigh an equal amount of sugar.

title: 6 week muffin mix
directions: Mix egg, sugar, soda and salt.
Add buttermilk, oil, beaten eggs and flour.
Stir in Raisin Bran.
Put in container and refrigerate up to 6 weeks for use as needed.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Whole batch makes approximately 60 muffins.

title: mock mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let set overnight in fridge.
Form into 2 or 3-inch patties.
Fry slowly in hot oil.

title: chicken l' orange
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Rinse chicken and place in a baking dish or Dutch oven.
Squeeze 2 oranges over it.
Salt and pepper or sprinkle with lemon pepper and soy sauce over bird.
Place in oven with no lid or tent of foil for 15 minutes, until slightly brown.
Lower temperature to 325°.
Bake for another hour, unless smaller bird is used.
Adjust cooking time to size of bird.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions.
Drain.
Add 1 package taco seasoning.
In bowl, blend sour cream, cream cheese and 3/4 package of taco seasoning mix.
Layer meat in oblong Pyrex dish. Sprinkle cheese over warm meat mixture.
Spread sour cream and cream cheese over.
Sprinkle with tomatoes, lettuce and cheese, then sprinkle olives.
Use dab of sour cream in center and circle it with salsa for decoration.

title: chili sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes and add salt.
Drain and let stand overnight. Chop celery, onions and bell peppers.
Add to tomatoes.
Cook slowly on stove until celery is done.
Add last 4 ingredients. Bring to boil.
Sterilize jars.
Bottle in sterile jars and adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Sift box of sugar.
Add cocoa.
Pour milk over mixture.
Lay stick of butter on top.
Don't mix.
Microwave 2 1/2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Add vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Put in freezer for 10 minutes.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix well; roll into 3 or 4 sticks.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Unwrap and bake at 300° for 1 hour. These may be frozen and then later sliced thin and served with mustard.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Dip broccoli in warm water to slightly thaw.
Combine mushroom soup and sour cream; mix well.
Place broccoli on bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour soup mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour
milk
into
a large mixer bowl.
Add pudding mix. Whisk until blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Stir in Cool
Whip
and
cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon of cookies in transparent plastic cups (need 8 to 10).
Fill cups 3/4
full with
pudding
mixture.
Top
with crushed cookies. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Decorate with peanuts and gummy worms and frogs.
Cute idea for a child's party.

title: muffin melt
directions: Top English muffin with Wham, sliced pineapple and shredded cheese.
Broil until bubbly.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookie dough.
Cool completely.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread on dough.
Add fruits over that layer one at a time.
Top with glaze and spread over fruits evenly.

title: spaghetti pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Beat eggs and milk.
Combine egg mixture with cooked spaghetti and place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Combine meats with spaghetti sauce; spread over spaghetti.
Layer remaining ingredients, topping with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: french dip sandwiches
directions: Remove and discard all visible fat from roast. Place in a slow cooker. Combine soy sauce, bouillon and spices; pour over roast.
Add water to almost cover roast. Cover and cook over low heat 12 hours or until meat is very tender. Remove meat from broth; reserve broth.
Shred meat with a fork.
Serve on hard rolls or French bread slices with broth. Yield: 12 sandwiches. Diabetic Exchanges: one serving (without roll, prepared with light soy sauce) equals 3 lean meats also, 175 calories.

title: meat balls in sauce for spaghetti
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, garlic, parsley, basil, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly and shape into balls 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Melt oil in a saucepan.
Brown the meat balls lightly on all sides.
Drain off the fat.
Add tomato sauce; cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti and pass the cheese.

title: spicy cranberry sundae pie
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust or store bought one.
Freeze. Combine first four ingredients, then stir into ice cream.
Spread into crust.
Freeze.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Saute onion in margarine. Add soup and milk; stir until smooth and thick. Stir in cooked potatoes. Place in well-greased casserole dish. Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Remove cover and
top with grated cheese. Put back in oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: pluckett
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Place into greased Bundt pan.
Boil butter, sugar and water. Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and beat with mixer.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add sour cream, pumpkin, all spices, vanilla, baking soda and flour.
Mix well.
Add raisins and chocolate chips.

title: oil pastry
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Pour oil and cold water into measuring cup (do not stir).
Add, all at once, to the flour mixture.
Stir lightly with fork.
Form into 2 balls; flatten dough slightly.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add buttermilk to sugar and butter. Beat eggs lightly and add to sugar and butter, stirring lightly. Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Cook 10 minutes at 375°.
Lower heat to 300° and cook until done, approximately 35 to 40 minutes.

title: old-fashion custard pie
directions: Pour
into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until done or until inserted knife is removed clean.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: nutty cream cheese spread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Chill 10 minutes.
Shape in a 6 x 1-inch patty and lightly coat with the pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: joyce's gingerbread
directions: Mix molasses, oil, sugar and eggs well.
Dissolve soda and add to molasses mixture with flour, cloves, cinnamon and ginger.
Add 1 cup hot water and stir slightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
(This also freezes well.)

title: white punch
directions: Pour the muscadine or scuppernong juice into punch bowl. Pour in as much Sprite as needed to fill. Add mold of muscadine or scuppernong juice ice. Replenish with Sprite. Mold will melt and add its juice.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients all together.
Put chopped nuts in bottom of greased-floured
Bundt
pan.
Add batter and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Some stoves may take 1 1/2 hours.

title: berta's homemade cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix yeast with 1/2 cup warm water; set aside.
Combine 4 cups of flour, salt, shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs with warm water.
Add yeast mixture.
Turn out onto floured surface, kneading in remaining flour.
Knead dough for 10 minutes.
Shape into ball in greased bowl.
Cover; let rise 1 hour.
Roll out on floured surface into big circle.
Pour melted margarine onto dough.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle.
Roll dough into a log shape; slice 1 to 1 1/2 inches thick.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen rolls.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix
flour,
sugar, shortening and salt.
Save 1/4 cup. Add remaining
ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for
35 minutes.
Sprinkle
crumb
mixture
on top after cake comes out of the oven.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberry sauce and pineapple in bowl; mix well.
Beat cream cheese in bowl until fluffy.
Fold in whipped topping.
Add to fruit mixture; mix well.
Spoon into salad mold or paper-lined muffin cups.
Freeze until firm.

title: no bake lemon cheese pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender or food processor and blend on high until mixture is thoroughly creamed (approximately 5 minutes).
Spoon into pie shell.
Garnish with grated lemon peel. Refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a large frypan saute onion, green pepper and rice in the vegetable oil until rice is golden brown.
Add water, tomato sauce, sugar, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Cover and bring mixture to a rolling boil.
Uncover and reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana date loaf
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Add syrup, egg whites, mashed bananas and chopped dates.
Pour into lightly oiled and floured bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.
Makes 1 delicious loaf.

title: cowpuncher stew
directions: Coat beef cubes with a mixture of 2 tablespoons flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
In Dutch oven brown meat on all sides in hot shortening.
Stir in the coffee, molasses, garlic, 1 teaspoon salt, Worcestershire, oregano and cayenne.
Cover, simmer over low heat until meat is almost tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add the 1 1/2 cups water, carrot slices, onion quarters and potato pieces.
Simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.
Blend 1/4 cup cold water into the 3 tablespoons flour, add to stew mixture. Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Serve in bowls.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spaghetti all amatriciane
directions: Cook onion and bacon together until onion is translucent and bacon is slightly brown.
Add tomato paste and "fry" a little. Add wine and cook down to half.
Add can of tomatoes, red pepper and salt and pepper.
Cook until tomatoes fall apart and juice is almost gone.
Grate cheese.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Toss spaghetti with sauce.
Pass the cheese.

title: polish sausage
directions: Boil wieners until firm; slice.
Heat vinegar, sugar, onion and peppers together.
Put in jars.
Cool and put in refrigerator. Ready to eat.
Keeps for days.

title: sin cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa.
Boil 1 minute only; add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until melted.
Add rolled oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: hot party sandwiches
directions: Slice through middle of all the rolls (lifting top as if making a large sandwich).
Mix poppy seed, onion, mustard and butter to make spread.
Cover bottom and top of bread with spread. Layer the ham, then the cheese on bottom of bread.
Place top layer of bread on top of ham and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Remove and slice into small sandwiches.

title: cinnamon-peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt and cinnamon. Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl. Beat with electric mixer until blended. Place bowl of batter, covered, in refrigerator to chill overnight before baking.
The next day:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Wet hands slightly and pick up a teaspoon of batter and roll it around in your hands.
Place the balls onto ungreased cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, just until lightly golden.
Do not overbake.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add sweet milk and beaten egg yolks. Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pastry.

title: ugly cookies
directions: Cook milk, raisins and nuts in saucepan until thick.
Stir constantly.
Spread on Ritz crackers and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix margarine and powdered sugar and ice cookies.
Store in airtight container.
Better if made ahead a couple of days before using.

title: bohemian loaf cake
directions: Cream sugars and Crisco; add eggs one at a time.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder, coconut and pecans.
Add alternately to cream mixture the dry mixture and milk.
Add flavorings and mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: fletch's flank steak
directions: Saute onion in olive oil until golden.
Add garlic; cook for 2 minutes.
Stir in red wine vinegar; reduce by half.
Add wine and beef broth; simmer for 5 minutes.
Cool marinade and pour over flank steak placed in a glass or ceramic dish.
Marinate in the refrigerator for 48 hours, turning steak every 12 hours.
Grill flank steak and baste using marinade.
Strain remaining marinade. Warm and serve as sauce.

title: bible cake
directions: Look up the scriptures in your Bible and you'll find the ingredients for this cake.
Beat together and bake at 200° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Yield:
8 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except corn, in blender.
Stir in corn and pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: egg casserole
directions: Scramble eggs with a little milk; cook until almost done.
Fold together all ingredients in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be assembled the night before.
Refrigerate.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in buttered glass baking dish.
Add sugar and water.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Cut in butter.
Add milk and mix.
Spread dough over peaches.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding supreme
directions: Put layer
of
vanilla
wafers in bottom of pan.
Slice bananas and
put
over
vanilla wafers.
Pour half pudding mix over this and repeat.
Mix Cool Whip, coconut and nuts together. Pour over top of pudding.
Refrigerate.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Can also use 1/2 teaspoon orange extract.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix beans, corn, chestnuts and onion together.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Add to vegetables.
Put in baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, margarine, shortening and eggs in a large bowl; stir in flour.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; roll balls in mixture.
Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until set, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
About 6 dozen cookies.

title: nana's banana nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease
and flour pan.
Mix cake ingredients in exact order
listed.
Use wooden spoon to blend and mix thoroughly.
Bake in small
tube pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Test with
toothpick
at
45 minutes.
Bake until cake is done.
If using loaf
pan,
bake
at
350° for 1 hour. Test same way.

title: apple dessert cake
directions: Generously cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with apples. Cream together 1 cup of sugar
and margarine.
Add milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread over apples in pan.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream butter 10 minutes or until very soft and fluffy.
Add sugar, two tablespoons at a time, creaming thoroughly after each addition.
Blend in vanilla and mace.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

Add flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour and beating after each addition until smooth. Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° about 1 1/2 hours or until cake tester inserted into cake comes out clean. Cool in pan 15 minutes; remove and finish cooling on rack.
Glaze top and drizzle down sides of cake with Orange Butter Glaze. Sprinkle with flaked coconut.

title: broccoli and cauliflower soup
directions: In saucepan, combine broccoli, cauliflower, water, salt and basil.
Cook until tender.
In separate pan, melt butter until lightly browned.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour over vegetable mixture and stir until blended.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add sugar and salt and beat until forms peaks.
Fold in chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Have oven at 350°.
Put cookie dough on ungreased foil by teaspoonfuls and place in oven.
Turn oven off and "forget" for at least 4 hours or even overnight.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter.
Add sugar, eggs (one at a time) mixing well after each one.
Add vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan, greased and floured.

title: easy ricotta cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour cake mix batter into pan.
Mix Ricotta, sugar, eggs and vanilla together; put this on top of cake batter.
Spread evenly; bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: ranch dressing
directions: For Dressing:
Mix 3 teaspoons of mixture with 1 cup mayonnaise and 1 cup buttermilk.

title: shrimp louis
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill.
Mound on tray and surround with crackers.
Enjoy.

title: no-fat honey mustard dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in wide mouth jar or small bowl, mixing until smooth.
Chill.
Store in a covered container in the refrigerator.

title: heath bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; cook to 290°.
Stir constantly. Cook to a golden brown.
Pour out onto cookie sheet.
Spread out as it cools.
Blot up excess oil with paper towel.
Melt the chocolate chips; spread over top.
Break into pieces.

title: cookie thang
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spray bottom of pan with Pam.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until thoroughly mixed.
The mixture will be thin, but will thicken as it cools. Store in the refrigerator.
One cup equals one can commercially prepared sweetened condensed milk.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: creamy pea salad
directions: Combine peas, cheeses, onion, mayonnaise, salt, and pepper; mix well.
Refrigerate until serving.
Sprinkle with bacon.

title: "my mama's" sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating each one well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream.
Pour batter into 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamed corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook on medium low for 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Mix butter and flour to paste.
Add paste mixture to corn mixture and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Put apples in bowl.
Mix with sugar and let set for 10 minutes.
Add oil and sugar mixture to eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to apple mixture.
Blend together by hand.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch pan, tube pan or 2 large loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool. Sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: lazy man cabbage rolls
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add garlic, onion and tomatoes; cook for 10 minutes.
Add rice and cook for an additional 10 minutes.
Peel off cabbage leaves and place in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add the first 5 ingredients.
Cover the top of the pan with cabbage.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: boiled cookies
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, margarine, cocoa, and milk. Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat then add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat well. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter well; add beaten egg yolks.
Add dry ingredients, alternately with milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Dice onion, then brown together with ground beef.
Drain off grease.
Add chili powder, flour, salt and sugar; mix until hamburger is evenly coated.
Drain kidney beans and tomatoes; add to mixture.
Cut tomatoes into pieces, if whole.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all 7 ingredients and refrigerate for 1 hour. Serve with chips.

title: sandy spring corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add corn, salt and milk and mix. Sprinkle grated nutmeg over top.
Bake until set and bubbling near center, approximately 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: In a heavy cast iron skillet, add 1 1/2 cups cold water to chopped cabbage.
Cook slow for 1/2 hour.
Check cabbage for tenderness.
Drain and add butter, salt and pepper.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook meat with onion and garlic until no longer pink; drain.
Add beans, red pepper, tomato sauce, taco sauce, salt and oregano.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Spoon 1 cup meat mixture evenly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer 6 tortillas over sauce; top with half of remaining meat mixture. Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Cover with remaining tortillas and meat mixture.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake for 20 minutes; uncover, top with remaining cheese.
Continue baking 5 minutes or until bubbly and cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Garnish with sour cream and cilantro, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: jackie collier's vegetable casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and put in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle broken crackers and butter on top.
Cook in oven at 350° until brown.

title: fluffy corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased or sprayed pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup reserved cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours.
Add water occasionally and mix just to keep juicy until last 1/2 hour.

title: sausage mushroom caps
directions: Heat the broiler.
Rinse the mushrooms. Scoop out stems with a small spoon and save for other uses.
Mix the pork sausage and bread crumbs. Mound meat mixture in caps, then place meat side up in a rimmed 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Broil 6 to 7-inches from heat until meat is well browned, about 5 minutes.
Lift mushrooms onto a platter. Scatter with Italian parsley leaves. Serves 12. Preparation time:
8 minutes.
Cooking time:
5 minutes.

title: skor candy bar cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Cook in 9 x 13 pan. As soon as cake comes out of the oven, pierce top with fork all over.
Pour caramel topping and milk over top of cake.
Top with candy bars.
Let cool, then top with Cool Whip and 1 Skor candy bar.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: egg nog
directions: Mix ingredients together in blender until foamy.

title: apple crisp cake
directions: Mix well together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients mixing by hand.
Bake in square pan, muffin pans or loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, depending on pan size. Let cool.
Freezes real good.

title: salsa
directions: Dice tomatoes in very small pieces.
Add cup tomato juice; core and remove seeds from jalapeno pepper.
Dice small red onion and mince garlic and chop fresh cilantro.
Combine all ingredients and mix together.

title: cranberry salad with cottage cheese
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and set in refrigerator. Once cooled and starting to thicken, mix in the other ingredients. Let congeal well before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: shrimp sausage jambalaya
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Put rice, green pepper and onions.
Slice sausage thinly.
Add to pan along with shrimp.
Add everything else, except margarine.
Put pats of margarine on top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken with hungarian paprika
directions: Cut chicken into parts.
Brown onion in shortening; add seasonings and chicken.
Brown 10 minutes.
Add water, cover and let simmer slowly until tender.
Mix flour with sour cream; pour over chicken and bring to a boil.
Serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Put raisins and nuts in bowl and mix with part of flour. Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, flour, lemon extract, raisins and nuts.
Put in large tube pan.
Bake at 275° until done (2 1/2 hours).

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli, set aside.
Melt butter, add flour and make a paste.
Cook 2 to 4 minutes. Add chicken stock, stirring with wire whip.
Bring to boil to thicken, turn heat to low.
Add broccoli, half and half, salt and pepper.
Heat on low, do not boil.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, margarine and sugar. Press mixture in bottom of a large casserole dish.
Slice bananas on top of the crumb mixture.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, beaten.
Last, add flour and vanilla.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour in oven at 350°.

title: out of this world pie(makes 2)
directions: In saucepan, combine cherry pie filling, sugar, pineapple and juice, cornstarch and food coloring.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Stir.
Allow to cool.
Add bananas and pecans.
Pour into baked pie shells and top with whipped cream. Chill.

title: party pinwheels
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle on remaining ingredients.
Roll and wrap tightly.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Cut off roll ends.
Cut rolls into 1-inch slices.
Makes 3 dozen.
Delicious appetizer!

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Can be used for pork, chicken or beef. Just mix and pour over meat to be barbecued and cook.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak the beans overnight.
Drain.
Pour into a soup kettle and cover with fresh water; add the potatoes and onion.
Fry the chopped salt pork until it crackles, then add to the pot. Sprinkle the soup lightly with salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil and let it simmer, covered, for 1 hour, stirring several times or until beans are tender.

title: onion short cake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Peel, dice and saute onion in butter. Set aside.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Arrange the cantaloupe, oranges, bananas, strawberries and grapes attractively on a large platter.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and press water out.
Mix all ingredients except broccoli and pour over broccoli (mix in a casserole).
Sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: melt aways
directions: Melt chocolates in double boiler and beat.
Add peanut butter and beat.
Line 8 x 8-inch pan with wax paper.
Pour candy into pan and smooth.
Place in a cool place, but not in refrigerator. Next day, cut in desirable pieces.
You may coat with melted chocolate if desired.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Add
sugar, corn syrup and water in medium saucepan and stir well. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Continue to boil to soft
ball stage. Add nuts.
Boil until mixture turns dark. Remove from heat and add vinegar, salt and baking soda. Stir well and
pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: banana pudding
directions: Blend pudding mix in milk with wire whisk.
Add sour cream and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Mix well.
In large glass bowl, layer half of mixture on bottom, then add half the cookies and half the Cool Whip and bananas.
Repeat layers.
Chill overnight.

title: grandma culver's goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add beans, chopped onion, tomatoes and macaroni; bring to boil.
Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Mix oleo and butter (on warm).
Add brown sugar and boil.
Add 1 cup pecans, then spread on cookies.
Bake.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: mrs. opal's dinner rolls
directions: Mix above ingredients using tablespoon.
Mix well.
Grease muffin pan.
Cook at 450° until golden brown.
Yields 12.

title: black-eyed pea of texas casserole
directions: Saute meat, onions and garlic until meat and onions are done. Drain off fat.
Use rectangular 9 x 13 dish. Place layer of meat mixture on bottom.
Next, lay corn tortilla strips on top of meat. Top with remaining meat mixture.

Sprinkle 1 cups shredded Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. (If you want to cute fat and calories, use light soups. If you use light cheese, add it 5 minutes before removing from oven, so it doesn't get leathery.)

title: britches patches
directions: Mix Pioneer mix and milk together until thoroughly blended. Roll out on floured board until about 1/4-inch thick. Cut into squares about 2-inches wide.
In a large skillet, melt 2 or 3 tablespoons margarine.
Brown the squares in melted margarine until brown on each side.
If margarine begins to burn, wipe out skillet with damp paper towel and use fresh margarine for next batch.
Serve with honey or Grandpa's Famous Maple Syrup.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain juice from cans and with a sharp knife cut across several times, cutting kraut so it will not be stringy. Empty into large mixing bowl and add celery. Mix together onion, red pimento, vinegar, green pepper and sugar. Let this set in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Thaw and drain frozen chopped spinach.
Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Add all the ingredients and mix well.
Put into a crock or a small baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.
Serve with crackers, bagel slices, taco chips or French bread.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together until smooth. Roll mix into balls and mash with fork.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: lemon herb butter for brussels sprouts or asparagus
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Add to Brussels sprouts just before serving.
Very tasty.
May be used on other vegetables.

title: forever wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a pint of Sympathy.
Flavor with Bright Fireside and Loving Kiss.
Bake well all your life.

title: maui mist(punch)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and chill.
Add chilled ginger ale and vodka (optional).
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: gumdrop coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in nuts, coconut and chopped gumdrops.
(If gumdrops are sticky, roll in about 4 tablespoons flour.)
Add vanilla.
Spoon into 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 300° about 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: oreo cookie freeze
directions: Mix together Oreos and margarine.
Pat mixture into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread ice cream on top and freeze until firm.

title: florida key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolk and salt until light in color.
Add sweetened condensed milk, stirring well.
Add Key lime juice and blend thoroughly.
(Note:
The lemon juice cooks the egg.)
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.
A variation on topping is either yogurt or sour cream to which a small amount of both sugar and vanilla are added and blended together.

title: turtle cake or snickers cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix according to instructions on box.
Pour half of the batter into the pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Over low heat, melt caramels, butter and milk.
Cool slightly.
Remove cake from oven and pour caramel mixture over half-baked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over caramel mixture. Pour rest of the batter on top.
Return to oven and bake an additional 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese delight
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and margarine together; press in bottom of 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients together and pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: daughter-in-law's curry
directions: Melt butter and saute onions and garlic in it for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add all the spices and the tomatoes.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes, still stirring often.
Add flour and stir constantly.
Add milk slowly and stir steadily until the boiling point is reached.
Add cucumber and meat.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Mix lemon juice and plum jam; add to curry and mix well.
Correct seasoning, if necessary.
Serve over rice.

title: beigneittes(fritters)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop ladle full into hot oil.
When both sides are light brown, take out.
Serve with powdered sugar, butter or maple syrup.

title: hurry up fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set pineapple aside. Combine bananas and pineapple juice; toss gently and drain. Combine bananas, pineapple, oranges and remaining ingredients in a medium bowl.
Toss gently.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and corn syrup.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients.
Last, add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna souffle
directions: Remove crusts from fresh slices of bread; break into small bits.
Scald milk and add to bits.
Add chopped cheese, tuna, lemon juice, salt and well beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into mixture.
Turn into buttered casserole.
Set into a pan of water and bake for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: "louise's" ricotta pie
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients together, then add the vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch Pyrex pie plate.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 35 to 40 minutes at 350° until center of pie feels firm.

title: "o' my!" bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 9 square pan. Sprinkle crumbs over this and pat down to make a crust. Layer all other dry ingredients and then pour condensed milk with salt added over all the other ingredients. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Cut while warm.

title: baked steak
directions: Pound round steak well.
Cut up in serving pieces.
Dip steak in flour.
Fry steak until brown on both sides.
Place steak in a roaster pan.
Pour (drained) mushrooms over steak.
Pour soup into frying pan.
Add small amount of milk (1/4 cup).
Stir until hot and smooth.
Pour over steak.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: autumn salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple. Add dry jello with Cool Whip. Add other ingredients, mixing well after each ingredient. Chill before serving.

title: hunter's beef
directions: Trim and discard fat from meat.
Cut into 4 to 6 serving size pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
With a mallet, pound seasoned flour into meat.
Heat oil in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat.
Add meat.
Brown well on both sides.
Scatter celery, mushrooms and 2/3 of green onions over meat.
Combine wine, soy sauce, ginger, cinnamon and red pepper in a cup.
Pour over meat.
Bring to a simmer.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender when pierced.
Scatter remaining green onions over meat.
Continue to cook, covered, for 5 minutes.
To serve, spoon vegetables and sauce over meat.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Place all ingredients in casserole dish and cover with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles about 25 minutes.
Drain and mix with oil. Arrange in a shallow 2 1/2-quart baking pan.
Make 3 layers of each, sauce, noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon, discarding skin and bones.
In a bowl, combine salmon, bread crumbs, chopped onion, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Combine milk and egg.
Add to salmon mixture and mix well. Shape into a loaf in a greased shallow baking pan or in a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: three fruit punch
directions: Tooth paste even zaps acne pimples.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt large candy bar, then mix with 9 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and top with 4 ounces Cool Whip.
Grate small candy bar and sprinkle over Cool Whip.
Chopped nuts may also be used to garnish.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix Bisquick, paprika, salt and pepper. Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Coat chicken in Bisquick mix and place (skin side down) in baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 15 more minutes or until done.

title: pace's tuna casserole
directions: Cook the macaroni; drain.
Boil eggs; cool and dice.
In a casserole (large) dish or pan, mix the tuna, eggs, salt, pepper and peas with macaroni.
Mix in mushroom or chicken soup. Sprinkle cheese or slice American cheese and place on top.
Put in oven at 400° for 20 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serve with a tossed salad.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Melt chocolate over boiling water; cool.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in butter, dry ingredients, milk and vanilla. Mix to dampen flour.
Beat 2 minutes with mix.
Add eggs, yolk and chocolate.
Beat 1 minute longer.
Grease and flour tube Bundt pan.
Pour batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.
Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: christmas breakfast
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Line pan with bread cubes.
Layer with corned beef, then cheese.
Add sauteed onion to egg, milk and pepper mixture.
Pour mixture over cubes, beef and cheese. Refrigerate overnight.

title: squash relish
directions: Boil and add drained squash.
Let simmer.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: apple pie
directions: Into unbaked pie crust, pour in apples.
Mix sugar and flour. Add milk and eggs; mix.
Pour filling over apples.
Mix softened butter, flour and sugar.
Sprinkle over top of pie.
Bake in a slow 300° oven for 1 hour or until crust is brown and filling is firm.
For apples or peaches you may wish to add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon to the filling.

title: bun bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter together; spread half in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Mix together the butter, milk and pudding; boil 1 minute.
Add powdered sugar; spread on chilled layer.
Mix peanuts in other half of chocolate mixture; spread on top.
Chill.
Cut into small pieces, as it is very rich.

title: mexican supper casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook onion and peppers in butter until tender; stir in chili, corn and olives.
Bring to boil.
Add cheese; stir to melt.
Pour into 11 x 7 x 1/2-inch baking pan. Prepare muffin mix according to directions.
Spoon dough in diagonal bands across top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: self crust chicken pie
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Put chicken on bottom; add chopped eggs.
Mix soup and broth.
Pour over chicken and eggs.
Mix flour, milk and melted butter.
Pour over the top of chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: california casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 2-quart baking dish. In a large skillet, in hot butter, saute onions about 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in hot rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly to mix well.
Layer the rice mixture in bottom of baking dish, then half the chilies.
Sprinkle with half the cheese; repeat.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes, or until bubbly and hot.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers; cover with boiling water overnight. Next morning, drain and pack cucumbers in jars.
Boil ingredients 5 minutes. Pour mixture over cucumbers. Seal. (Mixture for 4 pints.) Hot water bath 5 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in a skillet and cook until brown.
Drain.

title: baked cheese dip
directions: Mix and spread in an 8 x 8-inch or an oblong baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with Pepperidge Farm Butter Thins butterfly crackers.

title: fresh fruit ice cream
directions: To ice cream freezer container, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Freeze leftovers.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix liquid ingredients.
Add together with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Grease and flour the pans.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and seasoned salt in bowl; mix well.
Shape into balls. Roll in remaining 1 cup pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill overnight.
Serve with thin wheat crackers.
Yield:
64 servings.

title: beef and beans casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together in large frypan.
Drain excess fat.
Add brown sugar, molasses and pork and beans.
Cook 15 minutes and serve.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mom's easy baked beans
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together all ingredients until well mixed.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, or until heated thoroughly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar, lemon juice and herbal seasoning together and pour on vegetables.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.
May use a Ranch dressing in place of given dressing.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat the egg white until stiff and fold into mixture.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage until tender; drain and place in casserole dish. Set aside.
Fry onion and pepper in margarine.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons flour, then add evaporated milk.
Let come to a boil. Pour over cabbage.
Bake in oven about 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix together last 3 ingredients.
Pour over casserole and bake another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans and drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients, saving 2 slices of bacon for garnish.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: indian corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together adding muffin mix last. Bake at 350° 45-50 minutes.

title: ten-minute strawberry almond pie
directions: Bake pastry crust.
Combine 1 cup diced strawberries with cornstarch, sugar, water, lemon juice and food coloring.
Cook over medium heat until thickened (about 5 minutes).
Remove caps from remaining strawberries.
Place berries in pie crust, tips up. Chill.
Pour thickened mixture over berries. Top with whipped cream and almonds (if desired) just before serving. Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Pour over stuffing mix.
Coat over thoroughly.
Place a layer of stuffing on bottom of dish; add cooked chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over layer of chicken.
Finish up with remaining stuffing.
Pour a little of the chicken broth over to help keep it moist.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Combine soft shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar and soda.
Mix together.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 6 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: lefse
directions: Boil water, margarine, sugar and salt.
Remove from heat and add milk and potato flakes.
Mix well and chill for 12 or more hours (but not more than 24 hours).
Add 2 cups flour just before rolling out the lefse.
Form into balls, keeping them well chilled.
Roll out as thin as possible on a floured cloth covered board.
Use a rolling pin sleeve.
Lift with a lefse stick.
Bake on a hot lefse grill until brown spots are visible.
Flip over and bake so done on both sides.
Cover baked lefse immediately after baking.
Wrap in plastic when cool.
May be frozen.
Makes 50 rounds of lefse.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Melt butter, stir in flour and pecans.
Press in a buttered pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar in bowl.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread over baked, cooled crust.
Top with 1 cup of your favorite pie filling.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Shape into balls about 1/2-inch in diameter (bite size).
Place on wax paper or cookie sheet. Dust with additional powdered sugar.
Let dry (may take overnight). Dust again with powdered sugar.
Place in airtight container.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with persimmon pulp.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: my mom's (mary justus) southern corn
directions: Cream flour and butter together.
Add egg yolks, sugar and corn.
Fold in egg whites; add salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° until silver knife comes clean when inserted in the middle, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: new chili potato soup
directions: In soup pot, heat butter and saute onions.
When onions are soft, stir in flour and slowly stir in heated milk.
Stir constantly until mixture begins to bubble.
Reduce heat to low and add chilies and potatoes; salt to taste.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Scoop out 1 cup of potatoes and puree in blender and add back to pot.
Add jalapenos and cook 5 minutes more.
Serve with cheese on top.
If not thick enough, add instant potatoes. Servings:

title: s'mores
directions: Butter 9 x 9-inch pan.
Heat syrup and butter to boiling in 3-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Fold in cereal, 1 cup at a time, stirring gently until coated.
Fold in marshmallows.
Press mixture evenly in pan with buttered back of spoon.
Let stand until firm, at least 1 hour.
Cut into bars.

title: peggy's bread
directions: Add salt and sugar to flour.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in 4 cups of warm water.
Add 2 more cups of warm water as needed.
Mix well with hands.
Knead on a hard surface until it is all smooth and worked together.
Grease top in bowl.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down.
Let rise again.
Put in pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cajun style beans, rice and ham
directions: In large pot, melt margarine.
Add onion, 1/2 cup of the green onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook about 5 minutes until soft, stirring frequently.
Add chicken broth, beans, salt, pepper, bay leaves, basil, hot sauce and ham.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes, stirring often.
At end of cooking time, mash some of the softest beans against the side of pan to form a thick sauce.

title: gooey goop
directions: In medium bowl, combine glue, 1 cup water and several drops of paint or food coloring, stirring constantly.
In large bowl, combine the remaining water and Borax.
Stir until dissolved. Pour glue mixture into Borax mixture, stirring constantly.
A glob will form as you stir.

title: lentil shepherd's pie
directions: Put the washed lentils into a large saucepan.
Cover with water and boil gently until tender, about 45 minutes.
Drain. Preheat oven to 400°.
Use 1/2 of the butter or vegan margarine to grease a shallow ovenproof dish.
Saute the onions in the remaining butter or vegan magarine in a large saucepan for 10 minutes.
Add the garlic, mixed herbs, tomatoes, soy sauce, lentils, parsley, salt and pepper.
Spoon the mixture into the dish.
Spread the mashed potatoes evenly over the top, drawing the prongs of the fork over the surface to make ridges.
Dot the whole surface with a little butter or vegan margarine.
Bake for 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: ladyfinger delight
directions: In a 9-inch spring-form pan, stand Ladyfingers around edge and on bottom of pan.
Whip cream, vanilla and confectioners sugar; combine with Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Spread 2/3 of mixture on ladyfingers.
Place 1 layer of ladyfingers on top, then remaining mixture.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill 2 hours.

title: fruit macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain in a colander.
In one big bowl, mix macaroni, condensed milk and mayonnaise by using a spatula.
Blend thoroughly.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix carefully.
Chill for about 2 hours or overnight.
Serve cool.

title: pork chops and corn stuffing
directions: In an 8-inch square baking dish, combine all ingredients, except pork chops.
Brown pork chops (I usually trim off any excess fat).
Place pork chops on top of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning chops after 1/2 hour.

title: ...black gold and "texas tea"
directions: Combine the spices, sugar and 2 quarts of water in a saucepan; bring this mixture to a good strong boil.
Boil for 5 minutes. Add the tea and remove saucepan from the heat.
Steep for 5 minutes.
Strain.
Add the fruit juices plus 2 cans of water. Pour over ice in tall glasses.
Add lemon or orange slices for color.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: strawberry refrigerated dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries. Place into large Tupperware mixing bowl.
Mixture should fill bowl to 1/2 full.
If not, add some cold water.
Place in refrigerator until partially set.
Add angel food cake by placing into center of jello and pushing down into bowl.
Refrigerate overnight. Unmold and serve.

title: rosamarina fruit salad
directions: In medium saucepan add sugar, eggs, flour, salt, mandarin orange juice and pineapple juice and cook egg mixture until a custard consistency; cool about 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Drain well.
(This is a pasta that is shaped similar to rice.)
Mix macaroni with custard mixture.
Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve the juice.
Add cold water to make 1 cup.
Add boiling water to jello and stir 2 minutes.
Add juice and refrigerate 1 1/4 hours, until thickens like egg whites.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes or until it mounds. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put in a 6 cup mold.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Unmold.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt. Using electric mixer, cream together sugar and butter until light and fluffy; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Stir in sour cream and flavoring. Gradually mix dry ingredients into egg mixture until completely blended. Turn into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or divide mixture into 2 loaf pans that have been greased and floured.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift
together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Beat 2 minutes.
Add
oleo,
1/3 cup buttermilk and bananas;
beat 2 minutes more.
Add
eggs
and
1/3 cup buttermilk.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date loaf
directions: Separate eggs.
Cream yolks and sugar well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add 1/2 of the flour mixture to egg and sugar mix.
Use rest to dredge dates and nuts.
Add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add beaten egg whites.
Mix well.
