Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 300° until toothpick comes out clean; let cool.

title: glossy chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add chocolate, salt and water. Cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Spread while warm on 1 loaf or 9 x 9-inch cake. Frosting remains smooth and soft.

title: season greeter
directions: Combine juices.
Pour over ice in glass.
Add squeezed lime wedge.
Makes 1 serving.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add cherry juice.
Add drained pineapple, cherries and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream. Refrigerate.
Should be made 6 to 8 hours before serving time.

title: irma's fried chicken
directions: Mix together flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Mix beaten egg and milk.
Coat chicken with seasoned flour.
Dip in beaten egg and coat again with seasoned flour.
Melt Crisco into a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, until 1/4-inch depth is reached.
Cook chicken over medium heat.
Cover skillet tightly and simmer, turning once or twice, until the thickest pieces are done, 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove cover during the last 5 minutes of cooking to crisp chicken.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: turkey cutlets piccata
directions: Beat egg and milk; dip turkey, then dip in bread crumbs.
Over medium-high heat, melt 1 tablespoon margarine (more as needed); add cutlets and cook until brown on both sides.
Remove from pan. Reduce heat to low.
Squeeze juice of 1/2 lemon (or 1/2 ounce juice); add water and bouillon.
Return cutlets to skillet; put thin slices of lemon on cutlets.
Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes or until fork-tender.
Serve with pan liquid.
Serves 2.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion until tender.
Cook rice.
Drain both. Add soup, cheese and butter to rice, broccoli and onion. Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf with wild rice stuffing(serves 6)
directions: Combine ground meat, stuffing mix, tomato sauce, onion, celery, eggs, thyme and marjoram in a large bowl and mix well. Turn into a 10-cup Bundt pan, pressing meat against sides and center of tube pan to make well for filling.
Pierce rice pouch. Cook on High until just defrosted, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Layer mushrooms, rice and sausage in center of loaf.
Press edges of meat over filling, sealing to cover completely.
Cook on High for 14 to 16 minutes (microwave) or until probe set at 160° registers done or at 350° for 1 hour (regular oven).
Drain off accumulated juices.
Invert loaf onto serving platter.
Sprinkle top evenly with cheese and parsley just before serving.
(If necessary, cook on High just until cheese melts.)
Meat Loaf can be reheated.

title: chipped beef and egg brunch
directions: Pour boiling water over beef and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and shred beef in fine pieces.
Combine eggs with water and Tabasco sauce.
Beat with fork or whisk.
Melt oleo in a heavy skillet.
Add beef and saute.
When beef edges start to curl, add eggs.
Keep the heat on medium-low and with spatula keep scraping from bottom and sides of skillet.
Cook until desired doneness. Sprinkle with parsley and pepper.
Serve with muffins or whatever is your choice.

title: cheddar chicken bake
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Blend in flour and chicken bouillon cubes.
Gradually stir in milk, stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken and mushrooms.
Arrange broccoli in 2-quart casserole.
Spoon chicken mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: Put pork chops in crock-pot. Pour cream of celery soup over them. (Do not add water.) Cook on high for 4 hours.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Remove stem end from each tomato; peel tomatoes and cut into small pieces.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 teaspoons sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add half the flour and half the milk.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add remaining flour, salt, vanilla and milk, mixing until light and smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan.
Place in a cold oven.
Heat to 325° and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes; then turn out onto a cake plate.

title: seafood okra gumbo
directions: Saute the onion and okra in 1/4 cup oil until they are wilted. Add green pepper, celery and garlic; stir them until they are wilted.
In a skillet, add 2 tablespoons oil with flour.
Cook until brown.
Add to okra mixture.
Saute shrimp with remaining oil for about 10 minutes.
Add shrimp, oysters, bay leaves, crab boil, salt, tomato sauce and water.
Cook slowly for about 45 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add crabmeat.
Serve over rice.

title: red cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
Add to melted margarine in large heavy saucepan.
Toss lightly to coat cabbage.
Add peeled and diced apples, salt, pepper, vinegar, sugar and beer.
Cover and simmer gently, stirring as needed.
Cook until tender, about 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy fudge
directions: In saucepan, bring pudding, butter and milk just to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat quickly. Stir in 2 cups confectioners sugar, blending well.
Add 1/4 cup nuts.
Pour in greased 8 x 4-inch pan.

title: custard filled cornbread with corn kernels
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, sift together cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and pour in the buttermilk and eggs; stir until almost blended.
Stir in 1 cup of milk and the corn kernels until just combined.
Do not overmix.
Pour the butter in a 10-inch cast-iron skillet and heat in the oven until melted. Remove and swirl to coat bottom and sides.
Scrape batter into the hot pan and sprinkle with remaining 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and crusty on outside but still quivers slightly when the pan is shaken.
Cut into thick wedges and serve hot with sweet butter.

title: bean salad
directions: Rinse and drain celery, onion and pepper.
Cut up and add to beans.
Bring to boil sugar, water, oil, vinegar and salt.
Pour over vegetables and soak overnight.
Next morning, drain and serve.

title: banana quick bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts and blend; set aside.
Beat shortening until creamy , 300 strokes or 2 minutes at medium speed with hand mixer.
Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy
after each addition.
Add egg and beat until thick.
Add flour mixture and bananas alternately, blending thoroughly after each addition.
Fold in fruits and raisins. Grease bottom only (not sides) of 4 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Pour cherries in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle dry cake mix over cherries (do not stir).
Pour melted margarine over cake mix and sprinkle nuts on top; do not mix.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until set.
Top with ice cream to serve.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Reserve a few strawberries for garnish.
Wash and hull remaining berries; sprinkle with 1/3 cup sugar.
Mash slightly; set aside.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and place in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Place chicken on top and then sauce made with ingredients.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Last few minutes, cover with onion rings and leave in oven.

title: p.d.q. pickles
directions: Tie spices in cheesecloth bag.
In saucepan, combine spice bag, vinegar, sugar, salt and turmeric; bring to a boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour over vegetables; cool to room temperature.
Store in covered container in refrigerator (remove spice bag after 1 day).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon together and refrigerate until ready to serve.
When ready to serve, mix Sauce.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Add topping.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Mix in jello.
Fold fruit into mixture.
Chill.

title: not-neiman's cookies
directions: Blend oatmeal in a food processor or blender to a fine powder. Cream the butter and both sugars. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, blended oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add chocolate chips, candy and nuts. Roll into balls and place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake for 6 minutes at 375°.
Makes 112 cookies, but recipe can be halved.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove 1/2 cup of cookie dough and reserve for another use.
Add flour to remaining dough and knead with hands to combine.
Press dough into a greased 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool completely.
Blend cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla together until smooth.
Spread on cooled cookie.
Peel, core and slice (in thin slices) both apples.
Pour soda pop over apples to prevent browning.
Remove apples from soda pop and arrange on cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Heat caramel topping slightly and drizzle over whole pizza, then sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine.
Bake at 300° for one hour.

title: sugar cookies no. 1
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease two large baking sheets with butter or vegetable shortening.

title: nana's homemade chicken soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, put chicken, carrots, celery, onions, salt, pepper, and add enough water to fill pot 3\4 of the way. Cover, bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer 2 hours.
Remove chicken and cut into small pieces and return to pot.
In another pot cook your favorite soup pasta, drain and add to broth and serve with parmesan cheese.
Serves 6

title: vicky's refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix the boiling water, shortening, sugar and salt in a bowl. Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Add to the sugar mixture and mix well.
Stir in flour, form to a ball. Grease the top and cover.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled in size.
Punch down and cover.
Place in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Roll out on a floured surface, cut with biscuit cutter. Fold over and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: grace's cranberry salad
directions: Bring cranberries, water and sugar to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Add jello, then cool for 10 minutes.
Add grapes and pineapple, then cool for 5 minutes.
Add walnuts.
Refrigerate until set.
Will keep for days.

title: horseradish cheese ball
directions: In small bowl with electric mixer, blend cheese and horseradish until smooth.
Mix in salts and beef until well blended.
With hands, shape into a ball.
Wrap and refrigerate overnight or until firm.
Reshape and roll in chopped parsley. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. Cool and crumble. Cut broccoli into small pieces (raw). Mix mayo, honey and vinegar for dressing. Combine everything and add dressing just before serving.

title: pizza pan dessert
directions: Spread on pizza pan.
Bake at 300° until brown around edges, about 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: original nestle toll house chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls onto ungreased sheets.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: graham cracker tidbits
directions: *Be sure to use butter/margarine combination!

title: mom's quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put into an unbaked pie shell in this order:
cheese and onion rings mixed together and celery and green pepper mixed together.
Beat eggs until just blended; add milk and mustard.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings as soon as quiche comes out of the oven.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix together the soda and salt.
Cook sugar, water and syrup in a large pan until a thin thread will form.
Add peanuts and cook until peanuts stop popping.
Remove from heat and add soda and salt.
Pour into a large buttered pan.
Break when cooled.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef and onion together; drain well.
Combine all ingredients in a pot to simmer.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand (wooden spoon).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour
milk
into
large bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat with whisk
until
well	blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in whipped topping and half of crushed cookies. Place
1 tablespoon crushed cookies into cups.
Fill cups 3/4 full
with pudding
mix.
Top with remaining crushed cookies. Refrigerate for 1 hour; decorate.

title: round steak delight
directions: Place the steak flat on the counter.
Add the raw vegetables on the steak. Roll the ends up over the vegetables and fasten with long toothpicks.
Place the rolled steak in a flat baking dish and cover with foil.
Do
not season as the vegetables will do that. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Heat canned beef or mushroom gravy and pour over the ingredients.
Serve.
You may want to use leftover gravy instead of the canned.

title: ranch-style beans
directions: Fry hamburger first.
Drain.
Molasses is optional.
Then throw everything in crock-pot on low or on stove top at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: crab souffle
directions: Cut several pieces white bread into small pieces and cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Over bread, spread mixture of crabmeat, green pepper, onion, celery and mayonnaise.
Pour mixture of eggs and milk over the top and refrigerate overnight.

title: fresh dill tartar sauce
directions: Place all ingredients into a stainless steel bowl.
use a rubber spatula to stir tartar sauce.
Should be the consistency of 1000 Island dressing.

title: 15 minute jam
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover tightly and microwave 100% for 12 minutes.
Next, toss in blender and puree.
Spoon into refrigerator jars.
Great gift.

title: frosty snowballs
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Add the granulated sugar; beat until combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. Beat in water and vanilla until combined. Beat in as much of the flour as you can with the mixer. Using a wooden spoon, stir in any remaining flour and the chopped pecans. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place 1-inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 325° oven 20 minutes or until bottoms are light brown. Transfer cookies to a wire rack; cool completely.

title: spinach rockefeller
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Put back in pan; add cheese, stirring, over low heat.
Add garlic salt; pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters and roll in mixture of 3/4 cup of sugar and 3/4 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Pile in a greased Bundt pan. Melt oleo.
Add 3/4 cup of sugar and 3/4 teaspoon of cinnamon. Heat until sugar melts and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes, then invert on cake plate.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Drain syrup from peaches into pot and heat.
Blend 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt; stir into hot syrup.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Stir in margarine and almond extract.
Set aside.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 of pastry.
Lay peach slices on top and pour syrup mixture over peaches.
Roll rest of pastry thin; cut into 1/2-inch strips.
Arrange, lattice fashion, over top of dish.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over top crust.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 35 minutes, or until well browned.

title: potato soup
directions: Mash potatoes; mix all the ingredients together.
Bring to a boil.
Add butter and serve.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, shortening, nutmeg, brown sugar, cinnamon and salt until crumbly.
Take out 1 cup crumbs for topping; set aside.
Add baking soda to sour milk and stir.
Add to remaining crumbs the egg, baking powder and sour milk mixture.
Pour batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top, keeping crumbs lightly in center.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil and drain broccoli.
Add all other ingredients except cheese and bread crumbs.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Cook 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown ribs in a baking dish or roaster over surface heat. Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the ribs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes. Spoon sauce over the ribs during baking 2 or 3 times.

title: cheesy corn muffins
directions: Grease bottoms of 12 muffin cups.
In a bowl, combine flour, corn meal, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Blend well.
Add milk, oil and egg; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in corn and cheese.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix.
Measure 2 teaspoons of mix with cup of hot water.
Keep remaining in airtight container.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Prepare Good Seasons salad dressing mix according to directions on the package.
Pour dressing over all ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in covered casserole at 350° for 1 hour.
You can use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar at high speed with an electric mixer until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form and sugar is dissolved (approximately 2 to 4 minutes).
Add vanilla, beating well. Yields enough for one 9-inch pie.

title: punch
directions: In a large pan, bring water to boil.
Add sugar and stir to dissolve.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Before removing from stove, add jello and mix well.
Let cool.
Add juices and mix well.
Pour into two 1/2-gallon Ziploc freezer bags.
Seal and freeze until solid.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together; sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute onion and red pepper in butter until tender.
Cook noodles according to package.
Drain.
Add cheeses to hot noodles. Stir until cheeses melt.
Stir in onion mixture, peas and pepper. Spoon into greased baking dish.
Top with crackers.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave pecan clusters
directions: Melt candy in microwave. Add pecans. Drop on wax paper about 3 to 4 pecans in each drop. Let stand until completely cooled. About 2 to 3 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cake according to box and bake in a 15 x 11-inch pan for 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: yum-a-setta
directions: Brown hamburger with salt, pepper, brown sugar and onion.
Add tomato soup.
Cook egg noodles; drain.
Add cream of chicken soup and cream of celery soup to noodles.
Layer in casserole dish, hamburger mixture, cheese and noodle mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients and refrigerate overnight. Then combine dressing with remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: turkey roll
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over low heat, melt the margarine; add onion and celery.
Cook, stirring often until onion is golden. Stir in flour; add 1/2 cup milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat and add salt, turkey and Accent.
Set aside to cool while preparing dough.
In a small bowl, mix together the biscuit mix and poultry seasoning; add the 2/3 cup milk and mix to form a dough.
Roll to a 10-inch square.
Spread with the turkey mixture and roll up tightly; place seam down on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Brush top with extra milk and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Stir the sugar, cocoa and milk together and let them cook over a moderate fire until drops of the mixture harden in cold water. Then add the melted butter, marshmallow cream and the vanilla; beat as huskily as possible and pour on a greased platter.
Cut in squares as it cools.

title: pancakes
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, mix all dry ingredients, then add eggs, milk and butter.
Blend together until thick.
Turn stove on in between medium and broil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: squash boats
directions: Boil squash in chicken broth until tender.
Saute onions in margarine.
Cut squash in half.
Scoop out of boats and add onion. Add bouillon and seasonings and cook for 5 minutes.
Add cheese and cracker crumbs.
Reserve enough cheese to top each boat.
Fill boats with mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cold yellow rice salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Add 2 teaspoons chicken bouillon to boiling water and omit butter.
Cool.
Add to cooled rice the chopped artichokes, green pepper, olives and onions. Combine mayonnaise, curry powder and reserved artichoke liquid and add.
Mix.
Chill several hours.
Yummy!

title: potato-leek crock-pot soup
directions: Remove dark green part of leek and thinly slice remainder. Peel and cut potatoes into small dices.
Slice celery into small pieces.
Chop onions into small pieces.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans and soup, mix well. Pour into a baking dish. Sprinkle with onions. Bake at 350 for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Scald tomatoes, peel and core.
Place tomatoes in jar.
Put 1 teaspoon salt per quart on top.
Seal and place in oven on shelf second notch from bottom.
Bake at 250° for 65 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Layer in pan, starting with the graham cracker crust, then the mixture that's beaten, bananas, pineapple, whipped cream, nuts, fudge sauce in swirls and cherries on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sour cream candy
directions: Mix sugar, cream, syrup and salt.
Let come to a boil.
Cook gently without stirring to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add butter, cinnamon, almond extract and vanilla.
Let stand without stirring, until pan is just cool enough to be held on the palm of the hand.
Stir in nuts and beat candy until it loses its gloss and begins to "fudge".
Quickly pour into buttered pan. Let stand until firm; cut into squares.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook and drain ground beef; add taco sauce mix.
Cook with 1 cup of water until simmering.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix Bisquick and milk; blend well.
Pour over taco mixture.
Bake until breading mixture is cooked through.
Check with fork.
Remove from oven and add sliced tomatoes.
On top of tomatoes, cover with sliced Cheddar cheese.
Put back in oven until cheese melts.
Remove and add sour cream, then lettuce, onion, diced tomatoes and shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: You may grind in food chopper or chop fine cranberries, orange peel and apple.
Dissolve Jell-O in the 3 1/2 cups hot water. Pour over fruits.
Put in refrigerator to jell.

title: island teriyaki
directions: Combine soy sauce, brown sugar, oil, ginger, salt and pepper in deep bowl; mix well.
Cut steak into thin slices.
Add steak and water chestnuts to marinade; toss until coated.
Marinate for 2 hours at room temperature.
Thread steak strips on skewers, accordion fashion, alternately with water chestnuts.
Broil or grill over hot coals, turning frequently until done.
Yields 4 servings.

title: lasagna toss
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef with onion, garlic and salt. Stir in spaghetti sauce; simmer until heated.
Remove 1 cup of meat sauce; set aside.
Stir noodles into the remaining sauce. Place 1/2 of noodle-sauce mixture into greased 2-quart casserole. Cover with cottage cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Add remaining noodle-sauce mixture; top with 1 cup of reserved meat sauce and remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover; bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together.
Pour into suitable containers for freezing.
(Gallon size "Ziploc" bags work well.) Freeze.
To serve, scoop into glass; mix with ginger ale or 7-Up.

title: cheesecake ice cream
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar with an electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Beat in eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until blended well.
Stir in cream.
Freeze in a 4 or 5-quart ice cream freezer according to manufacturer's instructions.
Yield:
Approximately 3-quarts.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put into casserole.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salsa
directions: Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Pack in jars and seal. Very good.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix and
fill buns; place in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: rum pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well. Add flour and soda.
Add vanilla and rum flavoring.
Mix well. Add sour cream.
Cook at 325° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Cook for 1 hour and 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake in a tube pan.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles until tender, then drain.
Add peas, soup and milk.
Heat through a bit.
Add tuna.
Serve.

title: onions au gratin
directions: Cook onions in boiling salt water until tender.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter in pan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Add milk and cook, stirring until thick.
Add cheese, stir until it melts.
Combine onions and cheese.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and add bread crumbs until coated with butter.
Put on top of onions.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour together.
Rub in the shortening and then take out 1/2 cup of this mixture for the topping.
Add soda, sour milk and egg.
Mix well.
Mix in by hand the cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Grease and flour 2 pie pans.
Divide the mixture evenly into the 2 pans.
Top with the 1/2 cup flour mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, chocolate and flour; add egg yolks, slightly beaten.
Add milk slowly.
Add butter or margarine and cook until thickened.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell; cover with meringue and brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until fork pierces easily.
Peel potatoes and chop in large pieces.
While potatoes are still warm, mix in all other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender; drain well and mash.
Add salt and pepper.

title: jack cheese
directions: Soak gelatin in the 1 cup water in the blender while assembling remaining ingredients.
Pour boiling water over soaked gelatin and whiz briefly to dissolve.
Cool slightly.
Add cashews and liquefy thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Liquefy until mixture is the consistency of a creamy sauce, with no bits of carrot visible.
Pour into 1-quart mold; cool slightly.
Cover before refrigerating.
Refrigerate overnight before serving. After firming in the refrigerator, this "cheese" may be frozen until needed.
Makes 1 quart.
Tastes great on crackers!

title: egg white drop soup
directions: In a mekium sauce pan, combine water and broth mix.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Beat egg whites with a fork until slightly frothy.
Gradually pour egg whites into boiling soup, stirring briskly with the other hand, in a circular motion.
Pour soup into bowls.
Garnish with green onions.

title: chicken garden saute
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Sprinkle with rosemary; salt and pepper to taste, if desired.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover and cook 3 minutes over medium heat.
Uncover; cook over medium-high heat for 5 minutes or until thickened.
tags: Del Monte Italian style stewed tomatoes

title: date nut cake
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over 1 cup dates.
When slightly cooled, add 1 teaspoon soda to mixture.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and 3/4 teaspoon soda.
Add sifted flour mixture to shortening mixture.
Add date mixture; mix until blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Generously sprinkle top of cake mixture with sugar covering well, then sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rosemary walnuts
directions: Mix butter and seasoning together in shallow baking pan.
Add nuts, turning them in mixture to coat.
Heat 7 to 10 minutes in 350° oven, stirring occasionally.

title: apple pie
directions: Place flour, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Cut margarine into flour mixture.
Sprinkle dough with water and blend into dough until you can gather dough into a ball.
Half dough ball and roll on floured surface.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Lay chops in baking pan; cover with mushrooms.
Mix stuffing and cover chops.
Mix gravy with 2 cups of water and pour over stuffing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, peanut butter, syrup, vanilla, oats, baking soda, salt, M&M's and chocolate chips, beating after each addition.
Drop 1/4 cup dough on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press lightly to form 3 1/2-inch circle.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: canned dry peaches
directions: Cut peaches (not to thin).
Cover with sugar and vinegar and let stand over night.
Next morning cook down like preserves. Seal in sterilized jars.

title: italian pretzels(grandma bonvino's recipe)
directions: Place flour on work surface.
Make hole in center.
Add salt and fennel.
Work oils and yeast and
water into dough by kneading.
Knead
dough
for 15 minutes.
Let
stand
for
15 minutes.
Make Toda's:
Roll like
snake,
and
making
circle seal two ends together with fork.
Let Toda's rest 30 minutes, covered with a sheet.
Put large pot of
oil
water
to
boil. When water boils drop in Toda's for
minutes.
Remove
from water and place on top of sheet or
cloths.
Let
dry
turning often.
When totally dry, bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly golden brown.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; cover and let stand 20 minutes. Beat butter until creamy; gradually add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oat mixture; mix well. Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not remove cake from pan.

title: frontier hamburger stew
directions: Brown ground beef in a stewpan; drain.
Add tomatoes, 2 cans of water and bouillon cubes.
Cook until bouillon cubes are dissolved.
Add vegetables, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Simmer at least 30 minutes.
It is ready when vegetables are tender. Serve with grated cheese on top.

title: darrel's dip
directions: Empty all cans into crock-pot; set on high.
Add browned ground beef.
Stir.
Heat until all ingredients are hot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mamie eisenhower's fudge
directions: Boil sugar, salt, butter and milk for 6 minutes.
Put chocolates, marshmallow cream and nuts in a bowl.
Pour boiling syrup over ingredients in bowl; beat until chocolate is all melted and pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Let stand a few hours before cutting.
Store on a tin box.
This fudge is smooth and creamy.

title: lemon-basil chicken
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender except for basil.
Pour over chicken breasts and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake or grill.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Combine the flour, baking soda, salt, sugar and 6 tablespoons cocoa in a bowl.
Add the milk, vanilla and the margarine; beat until smooth, then add the nuts.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together the brown sugar and 1/2 cup cocoa; sprinkle over the mixture.
Pour the boiling water over the mixture in the baking dish, then bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
The top layer will be cake and the bottom, pudding.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Pour Italian dressing over warm potatoes.
Chill for 2 hours; add celery, onions and eggs.
Mix with mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: tinker burgers
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet until browned; drain if needed.
Add soup and mustard.
Heat about 5 minutes.
Spoon into hamburger buns.
Wrap each burger in foil.
May be served while hot or refrigerated for later use. May be frozen up to 2 months.
Fast and easy to make.

title: deer stew with mushrooms
directions: Use a heavy kettle and heat bacon bits.
Add deer meat and saute with paprika until brown on all sides.
Add 3 or 4 cups boiling water.
Stir occasionally to keep meat from sticking. Cook over low heat for 2 hours.
Add potatoes and onions during last 30 minutes of cooking time. Remove meat, potatoes and onions. Keep warm.
Make a thickening of about 3 tablespoons flour and broth.
Stir into juice.
Add meat, mushrooms, potatoes and onions.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup of juice.
Mix flour, sugar and cheese and stir into pineapple.
Pour juice over all.
Pour in an 11 x 17-inch dish.
Blend butter and crushed crackers. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken breasts parmesan
directions: Mix butter and buttermilk.
Then roll chicken in bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and garlic salt.
Roll up; put in baking dish.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix well; chill in refrigerator. Before serving, sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Mix the shortening and sugar, creaming well.
(I use mixer.) Blend in eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add the banana, mixing well.
Blend in the sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pan.
Push batter up into corners of pan, leaving center slightly hollowed. For a well rounded loaf, allow to stand for 20 minutes before baking.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool thoroughly on rack before slicing.
Serve plain or with butter or cream cheese.

title: sausage rolls on grill
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until it crumbles. Drain and cool. Place biscuits on floured pastry board; flatten and pinch seams together. Roll into an 8 x 12-inch rectangle. Sprinkle sausage and remaining ingredients on rectangle. Roll to enclose filling; seal edges. Cut into 6 slices. Place slices in 2 disposable baking pans. Grill with lid down over medium indirect heat for 30 to 35 minutes or until rolls test done.

title: easy skillet beef n' pasta
directions: Cook ground round in a large skillet over medium heat 8 minutes, stirring until it crumbles and is no longer pink; drain well and return to skillet.
Stir in 3 cups of water and bring to a boil; stir in pasta.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer, stirring often, 15 to 18 minutes or until pasta is tender.
Stir in pasta sauce; sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Cover and cook 4 to 5 minutes or until cheeses are melted.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, butter, eggs and bananas together.
Add flour, salt, soda, vanilla, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° to 350° for about 1 hour or until cakes springs back when touched.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut into bite size pieces the first 4 ingredients.
Mix together; scatter peas on top.
Put dressing over top.
Seal tightly and let set for 24 hours.
Mix well before serving.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in large skillet and stir while cooking. Cook to soft-ball stage and set off the stove to cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Beat with mixer until thick.
Add nuts and drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: italian spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Grind beef and pork together.
Brown meat, onion, parsley and garlic in about 3 tablespoons of oil.
Add cheese and oregano (mushrooms, too, if you like them).
Add all ingredients to tomato mixture.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook for about 2 1/2 hours on low heat.

title: waldorf astoria cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs and add to creamed mixture. Add melted chocolate.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add alternately with liquid ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan 13 x 9 x 2-inch, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: In a bowl, combine gelatin and hot water.
Let cool, then add pineapple and strawberry pie filling.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch glass dish; chill until set.
Soften cream cheese and mix with sugar. Blend in sour cream.
Spread over gelatin mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: mom's fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in pot on stove.
Boil for 5 minutes on medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Set off stove and immediately add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered pan. Chill before cutting.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into serving pieces. Combine 2 tablespoons flour and salt; coat steak with flour. Brown in hot oil in skillet.
Place in a lightly greased baking dish.
Add 2 tablespoons flour to pan drippings.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes, celery, carrots and onions; cook until thickened.
Stir in soy sauce.
Pour over steak in baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until steak is tender.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix well; will be stiff.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: jello-ring salad
directions: Beat together until thick.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Add all liquids.
Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix for 2 more minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Dissolve ammonia in milk at least 1/2 hour before baking. Cream the shortening and sugar until fluffy. Add beaten eggs.

Mix well. Add part of flour and salt alternately with milk mixture and oil of lemon. Mix well, adding flour until dough is easy to handle. Roll out about 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick. Cut out and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, just until they are lightly brown. Cookies can be frosted.

title: apricot dip melon balls
directions: Spoon cantaloupe balls.
Chill.
Combine rest of ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Chill.
When ready to serve, put cantaloupe balls into lettuce cups and spoon dip over the melon balls.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Set ice cream out to soften.
Crush 60 Ritz crackers.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Reserve about 3/4 to 1 cup cracker mixture.
Press remaining crackers into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir ice cream, pudding, milk and Cool Whip together.
Pour ice cream mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining cracker mixture on top of dessert.
(Note:
Any flavor of ice cream and pudding can be used.) Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Chop up the ham and onions.
Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate several hours before serving. Serve on snack crackers.

title: taco soup
directions: After browning ground beef and onion, mix all ingredients together and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve with cheddar cheese, sour cream and tortilla chips broken up.

title: prune cake
directions: Steam prunes 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix all dry ingredients and nuts together.
Mix eggs, oil and buttermilk and add to dry ingredients.
Blend and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: down and dirty tortilla soup
directions: This recipe can be prepared in the crock pot in the morning. Put the onion, garlic, cumin, tomatoes, Rotel and chicken in the pot.
You can leave the chicken whole or cut up.
It will shred after it's cooked when you stir the soup.
Chop or cut the cilantro.
Set stems aside for garnish.
Cook over low heat for several hours or speed up the process if you're cooking over stove for a quick meal.
About 20 minutes before you serve, heat the tortilla chips at 225 degrees for crispy chips.
Serve a heap of shredded cheese on hot soup and garnish with diced cilantro stems for flavor and texture.
Serve with warm tortilla chips.

title: daughter-in-law candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk 3 minutes.
Take from fire.
Add vanilla, coconut and crackers.
Add pecans if you like.

title: play dough
directions: Heat together when mixture pulls away from the pan, remove it from the heat.
Knead the Play Dough and store in an airtight container.

title: quick reuben
directions: Combine cabbage and marinade in resealable plastic bag. Refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight.
Layer 1/4 marinated cabbage, turkey and cheese on each of 4 rye slices. Top with additional slice of bread.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain and cut into pieces and arrange in greased baking dish.
Cover the broccoli with the chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with the shredded cheese.
Combine stuffing mix with melted butter and sprinkle over the top.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Lay strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 350° to 400° until baked.

title: green bean - corn casserole
directions: Layer green beans and then the corn.
Mix cheese, onion, sour cream, water chestnuts and celery soup.
Spread over vegetables. Combine 1 stick margarine, melted, with 1 stack Ritz crackers, crushed and sprinkled on top.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken rice fiesta
directions: Saute onions and pepper in margarine.
Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together and put into casserole dish.
Cover top with crumbled crackers.
Melt 1 stick margarine and drizzle over top. Bake 20 minutes.

title: algia's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat in greased pan. Cook at 375° until an inserted toothpick comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes and cut into squares.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Combine cocoa and soda in large bowl; add 1/3 cup margarine. Add boiling water and stir until well blended.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining margarine.
Add flour, vanilla and salt; stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Grease jelly roll pan.
Line with wax paper.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake at 375° for about 13 minutes, no longer.
Roll cake with waxed paper still on and wrap in a towel.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
After cool, remove wax paper from cake and unroll.
You are now ready to spread filling on.

title: noodle-sour cream casserole
directions: Combine 1 cup sour cream and cottage cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix this with cooked noodles.
Put mixture in shallow casserole.
Spread with remaining sour cream and sprinkle thickly with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
Delicious.

title: bridge party chicken sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread on buttered white bread.
Cut into small sandwiches.
Serve with soup and a salad.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Remove seeds from chile peppers.
Combine all ingredients. Place in double boiler to heat.
Serve hot with large Fritos.
Can be doubled.

title: mexican rice
directions: Over medium heat, brown rice in drop of oil.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Stir in Knorr. Reduce to low heat, and do not cover until you can see the rice.
Cover and cook until rice is tender.

title: chicken bride and groom
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Saute celery and onion in 1/2 stick butter and spoon over the shredded chicken.
Pour 1/2 cup broth over and add the sour cream and cream of chicken soup mixture over it.
Then cover with bread crumbs and pour 1/2 stick butter over the top.
Add 1/2 cup chicken broth, if desired, to moisten crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Sift remaining ingredients together.
Mix all ingredients together until creamy.
Add 1 cup boiling water very slowly.
(Batter will seem runny.)
Bake at 300° to 325° approximately 40 minutes to 1 hour depending on your oven.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls 1 1/2-inches.
Brown in 2 tablespoons fat with small garlic clove.
Cover with rest of soup and 1 cup water.
Simmer about 40 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix cheese, cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press firmly in bottom of a buttered 8 x 10-inch glass casserole dish.
Add asparagus liquid to the soup.
Arrange asparagus over the cracker crust.
Sprinkle over this the nuts, then add the soup mixture. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
After removing from oven, let stand a few minutes before serving.
Yields 10 generous servings.

title: cranberry-carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease three 8-inch round baking pans; set aside.

title: classy chicken
directions: Combine soups, milk, chilies, onion and chicken.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, arrange 2 layers of corn chips, chicken mixture and cheese in that order.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until piping hot.
Yields 6 servings.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: fruit slush
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Add the rest of ingredients and freeze.
Stir a couple of times a day.
To serve, fill glasses 2/3 full of slush, then fill glasses with 7-Up.
Coordinate fruit and Kool-Aid flavors.

title: easy pork chop dinner
directions: In electric frypan, spray with cooking spray.
Brown pork chops on one side, turn.
Place a slice of onion, a green pepper ring and 1 tablespoon uncooked rice on each pork chops.
Pour a can of tomatoes over all.
Add water or tomato juice to make enough liquid to cook rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook at 300° until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Have strawberries thawed and strained (save juice).
Dissolve jello in hot water and add 1 cup juice.
In a large bowl combine and mix drained pineapple, drained strawberries and nuts.
Fold in jello.
Pour 1/2 into refrigerator bowl (dish) and let sit until firm.
Then cover with sour cream mixture.
Add other 1/2 cream mixture and let sit in refrigerator.
Recipe may be halved.

title: pizza burger
directions: Brown
ground beef; drain off fat.
Add pizza sauce and simmer 15
to 20 minutes.
Place buns (open) on cookie sheet. Place hamburger
mixture
on
each
bun
and top with cheese. Place under broiler until cheese melts.
Serve open-face.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk and set aside.
Mix cake mix, butter, milk and pecans.
Put half of mixture into greased pan. Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Then pour caramel mix over cake, then put chocolate chips over caramel, then the rest of cake mix.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, add butter, sugar and 1 egg at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients; alternate with milk.
Mash 1/2 cup of blueberries and add to mix.
Stir in the rest of blueberries. Grease muffin tins (tops also).
Sprinkle sugar on top of muffins. Enjoy.

title: other best pie crust
directions: Melt butter in boiling water; blend in flour.
Make day before needed; it will keep a few days.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and freeze.
Partially thaw for 2 to 3 hours before using.
Mixture should be slushy. Break up and add the ginger ale to this.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
In a casserole dish, put vegetables in bottom, then hamburger meat.
Add gravies on top.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: german sauerkraut
directions: Put all ingredients into a large pot with tight-fitting cover. Bring to boil and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
It does not have to boil, but should not come out of the cooking stage.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Saute onions and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: eight layered salad
directions: Tear up lettuce.
Cook bacon well and crumble.
Layer salad in bowl as follows:
lettuce, celery, peas, mayonnaise, eggs, onion, grated Cheddar or desired cheese and bacon.

title: butterscotch rounds
directions: Melt
tablespoons
margarine
in 14-inch Dutch oven. Sprinkle brown
sugar
and	pecans over margarine.	In a large mixing bowl,
dissolve
yeast
in
hot
water.
Add 1 1/3 cups flour and the remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining	 flour.
Drop	 batter
by
tablespoons
over butterscotch mixture.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place.
(Dough will not
double.)	Heat
Dutch
oven,
14 coals on top and 12 coals on bottom.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately
invert on serving dish.
Let oven remain inverted so butterscotch-like topping will drizzle over coffee cake.

title: grandma lillie's chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add cocoa; stir.
Add sugar; mix with electric mixer.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve plain or top each slice with vanilla ice cream or Cool Whip for an extra tasty treat.

title: bachman wild rice casserole
directions: Place the cooked rice in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Saute the onion and mushrooms with salt, poultry seasoning and pepper in butter about 3 minutes.
Add this with the chicken broth or beef bouillon to the rice in casserole, stirring well.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 30 minutes.
Remove the cover, fluff with a fork and bake, uncovered, a few minutes longer, or until any excess moisture is absorbed.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
In the bacon drippings, cook onion just until tender, not brown.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: charlie chaplin candy
directions: Cut marshmallows in half.
Melt chocolate in large glass mixing bowl in microwave for about 2 minutes.
When chocolate is melted, fold in marshmallows.
Mix.
Put on aluminum foil in refrigerator to cool.
Cut or break into pieces.

title: mutt's shrimp
directions: Take a big wash tub.
Fill with water and add crab and shrimp boil and salt.
Add potatoes, onions and Polish sausage.
Cook about 15 minutes at slow boil.
Add plenty of corn-on-the-cob. Cook about 15 minutes more.
When onions and potatoes are fork-tender, add shrimp.
Cook until pink, about 5 to 8 minutes. Dump all out on newspaper on picnic table.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Roll in balls the size of walnuts; dip in sugar. Place on cookie sheet.
Press down with glass dipped in sugar. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: pretzel salad
directions: For first layer, mix first 3 ingredients and spread in 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
For second layer, mix next 3 ingredients and spread on top of first layer.
For third layer, dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water;
add strawberries and mix.
Chill until almost congealed, then spread on top of cream cheese and Cool Whip mixture.
Continue chilling until set.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Empty 1 can of beans into bottom of a greased casserole dish. Combine sugar and mustard; sprinkle half of mixture over beans. Top with remaining can of beans.
Sprinkle remainder of sugar-mustard mixture over beans.
Next, put chopped bacon and the ketchup over the beans.
Bake in slow oven (325°), uncovered, for 2 1/2 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: rice pudding 2
directions: Melt margarine in large pot.
Stir in sugar and rice.
Add milk and vanilla.
Bring to boil then simmer for one hour.
Remove from heat and add eggs, beat each one separately and add.
Put into bowl and sprinkle cinnamon.
Cool for a few hours before serving.

title: mexican mess
directions: Microwave burritos on a large plate for 3 minutes, turning once.
Cut burritos into 1-inch chunks.
Top with cottage cheese and salsa.
Mix.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain cherries and reserve the juice.
Blend softened cream cheese and mayonnaise with mixer.
Slowly add juice reserved from cherries.
When blended, fold in Cool Whip.
Cut cherries in halves and add to mixture.
Add pineapple, nuts and grapes.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place in freezer at least 3 hours. Remove 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Alternate flour and milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake in tube pan or 3 (8-inch) cake pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown (approximately 1 hour) for tube pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, beaten well.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Add carrots and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf or tube pan 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350° or in three 8-inch layer pans for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Icing. This cake also is good as a pound cake without icing.

title: carrot marmalade
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight.
In the morning, boil slowly, stirring frequently until thick.
Seal hot.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Mix 3/4 of beef with other ingredients.
Form into a ball. Roll in remaining beef and serve on crackers.

title: french fried onions
directions: Cut cleaned onions into 1/4-inch slices.
Separate into rings. Dip onion rings in milk and then in seasoned flour.

title: "good" slaw
directions: Mix oil, sugar, apple cider vinegar and seasoning from Ramen noodles. Let stand for 1 hour. Pour over slaw mixture. Just before serving, add crunched up Ramen noodles (dry).

title: batter dipped sandwiches
directions: In bowl with fork, beat together flour, baking soda, salt, oregano, basil and beer until well blended to make batter.
Cut cheese, ham and turkey slices in half crosswise.
Spread mustard evenly on one side of each bread slice.
Top mustard side of 4 bread slices with cheese, ham and turkey slices, dividing evenly and trimming to fit.
Place remaining bread slices on top, mustard side down to make 4 sandwiches; press each sandwich gently to seal.

title: 10 day salad
directions: Drain all canned ingredients and chop pepper, celery and onions. Mix together in a large bowl. Heat sugar, oil, vinegar and salt until sugar is dissolved. Pour over ingredients. Make 24 hours ahead of time to marinate. Will keep in refrigerator 10 days.

title: pumpkin pie with meringue
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pie crust with a fork.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes on lowest rack.
Combine pumpkin, egg yolks, sweetened condensed milk and the next 6 ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes in center of oven.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice, not too thick.
Cook just until tender and drain.
Add butter, sweet milk and flour.
Mix well. Cook.
Put a layer of potatoes and a layer of sauce.
Repeat until all is used.
Put in oven and bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini honey muffins
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir all together just until moistened.
Pour into greased muffin tin. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: curry glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in honey, mustard, curry and salt.
Add chicken, turning to coat. Bake 20 minutes and turn chicken.
Continue baking 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: venison chili
directions: Brown venison in vegetable oil.
Add onions, garlic powder and green peppers.
Cook five minutes, stirring constantly.
Add chili powder, sugar, tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and salt.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
If a thicker chili is desired, stir in one tablespoon flour mixed with two tablespoons water.
Just before serving, add kidney beans.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: raisin sauce(serve over slices of baked ham)
directions: Combine 3 cups water, raisins, sugars, lemon juice, nutmeg and salt in a medium saucepan.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Add the butter and stir until it melts.
In a small bowl, combine the cornstarch and remaining 1/3 cup water.
Add it to the bubbling sauce and cook until the sauce thickens.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: ranch beans
directions: Drain beans; set aside.
Cook bacon; remove from pan and crumble.
Add to beans.
Cook onion in bacon grease.
Drain and add to beans.
Add remaining ingredients to beans; mix well.
Bake in a large covered casserole for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: skillet potatoes
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook celery, onion and garlic in butter until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add broth, water, potatoes, carrots and pepper to skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Uncover; over medium heat, simmer 5 more minutes or until broth is slightly thickened, stirring often.
Sprinkle with fresh parsley, fresh chives or sesame seed before serving.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: fruit shortcakes(diabetic recipe)
directions: Mix ingredients until soft dough forms.
Spoon dough into 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 425° or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut in 12 squares.
Top with favorite fruit (berries, peaches or fruit cocktail).
Remember the fruit counts too!
One square equals 1 starch.

title: peach bavarian
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 1/3 cup syrup.
Dissolve jello, sugar and salt in boiling water; add the syrup.
Chill until slightly thick.
Chop peaches.
Blend extract into Cool Whip.
Beat jello with mixer, then add Cool Whip and beat until well blended.
Fold in peaches.
Chill.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and milk; cook on stove until thermometer reaches 236° (soft-ball stage).
Remove from heat. Add margarine; cool syrup until lukewarm (110°).
Add vanilla, peanut butter and nuts.
Beat until candy begins to thicken and loses its high gloss.
Turn immediately into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: rhubarb bread pudding
directions: Mix sugars together.
Layer bread, half the rhubarb and half the sugar into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with spices and raisins.
Repeat, ending with bread on top.
Pour hot milk over all.
Beat 4 eggs slightly and pour over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar, cream, syrup and salt.
Cook on medium heat. Stir until sugar dissolves, then cook until soft-ball stage. Remove from heat and let cool for at least 10 minutes.
Add peanut butter and vanilla flavoring.
Beat until gloss is gone.
Pour in 8-inch square pan.

title: cheddar bread
directions: Combine mix and cheese.
Mix eggs and milk.
Stir into cheese mixture just to moisten.
Bake in greased and floured 5 x 9-inch pan for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together, put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: dirt cake
directions: Prepare pudding as directed and set aside.
Mix together sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Layer all mixtures, ending with crushed Oreos.
Chill.

title: vanilla chiller
directions: Place the coffee and chocolate in blender container. Cover and blend on high speed until chocolate is chopped into small pieces. Add the ice cream; cover and blend on high speed, using on/off action, until smooth. Pour into 3 glasses. Top each serving with 2 tablespoons thawed Cool Whip topping. Serve immediately.

title: easy peanut butter roll candy
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix icing and powdered sugar until stiff enough to handle by hand.
Place powdered sugar on aluminum foil and knead mixture.
Flatten mixture by hand.
Spread peanut butter.
Roll to form log.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: salsa
directions: Blend all ingredients except spices in food processor.
Pour into large mixing bowl and add spices.
Pour up into jars and store in refrigerator.
Serve for dipping with taco chips.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix meat, onion, egg, garlic, rice, salt and pepper in bowl. Separate cabbage leaves and lay in pan of boiling watar to soften.
Lift out leaves.
Fill with a ball of meat mixture.
Roll cabbage around meat and fasten with toothpicks.
Place in pot. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover well with water.
Bring to a boil, then turn down heat and simmer about 2 hours.

title: broccoli and eggs au gratin
directions: Trim off large leaves and tough ends of lower stalks of broccoli.
Wash broccoli thoroughly and separate into spears. Cook in a small amount of boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender.
Arrange broccoli spears in a greased 2-quart baking dish. Top with eggs and cheese.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly. Stir in Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pour sauce over broccoli mixture.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a heavy saucepan; stir in bread crumbs.
Brown lightly and sprinkle over sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: cajun baked fish
directions: In a skillet, fry onion and garlic in butter over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Add tomatoes, thyme, bay leaf, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and Tabasco sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Add green beans and heat again.

title: microwave english muffin loaf
directions: Combine 4 cups of flour, sugar, salt, soda and yeast.
Heat liquids until very warm (125° to 130°).
Add to dry mixture and beat well.
Stir in rest of flour to make stiff batter.
Spoon into 2 loaf dishes (glass) that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Sprinkle tops with cornmeal.
Cover and microwave on Medium power for 1 minute.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Repeat cooking and resting, allowing dough to double in size.

title: party chicken
directions: Line chipped beef in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Wrap bacon around each breast.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken. Bake at 275° for 2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Stir mix, eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla and 1/2 oleo.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar, cinnamon, pineapple and rest of oleo.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine all ingredients.
Place dough in covered bowl in refrigerator.
There is no need to let rise before baking.
Drop by spoonful into greased muffin tins to bake.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: true-blue chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare shallow baking dish with vegetable oil cooking spray.

title: best sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, cream of tartar and soda together.
Mix butter and sugars until creamy.
Add oil and vanilla.
Mix in flour, cream of tartar and soda.
Chill 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, milk, garlic salt, pepper, onion, rice and meat. Mix thoroughly.
Press about 1/2 of mixture into a greased 9 x 5 inch loaf pan.
Place cheese on meat.
Spread remaining mixture over cheese, being certain cheese is completely covered.
Spoon barbecue sauce over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Let stand at room temperature for 5 minutes before slicing.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles and drain.
Mix other ingredients and add to noodles.
Pour into ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes at 350°; cook, uncovered, an additional 10 minutes.
Serves at least 2.

title: applesauce raisin muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: easy cocktail franks(serves 10 to 12 people; great for buffets or covered dish supper)
directions: Slice franks into 1/2-inch pieces and place in crock-pot.
Mix other ingredients and pour over franks.
Simmer in crock-pot for 4 hours on low.

title: raspberry torte
directions: Split cake into three layers.
Spread bottom layer with 1/3 cup jam.
Spread on 1/3 of Cool Whip.
Repeat.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: lemon velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix, lemon pudding, eggs, vegetable oil and water with mixer for 10 minutes on medium speed.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 1 minute.
Prick cake all over with a fork.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar and salt.
Pour ingredients into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake in slow oven (300°) 1 hour, stirring several times.
Add lemon peel, nutmeg and raisins; continue baking 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter in a double boiler.
When melted, add peanuts and potatoes.
Spoon on waxed paper and leave for several hours, overnight is good.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas; blend in sugar, salt and beaten egg.
Melt butter and stir into banana mixture.
Dissolve soda in water and add with sifted flour.
Mix and bake in loaf pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: delmarva chicken royal
directions: Place chicken in pan or baking dish.
Melt butter.
Add wine, honey, chopped parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well and brush mixture over both sides of chicken.
Add mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until tender and delicately brown.
Place chicken in serving dish along with the mushrooms.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Serves 4.

title: reese's chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
(Do not overbake; cookies will be soft.
They will puff while baking and flatten while cooling.)
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix together until smooth. Unroll cooled roll; spread filling and roll up. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate snowflakes
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add about 1/4 of dry mixture at a time to wet mixture, mixing after each addition. Cover and chill dough at least 2 hours.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Place cookies 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Yield:
8 dozen.

title: stir-fried beef and vegetables
directions: Combine steak, garlic, soy sauce and ginger.
Heat oil in large skillet or wok; add meat mixture.
Cook just until all pink color disappears.
Add vegetables; stir quickly to coat with oil, then reduce heat to medium.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring once. Mix cornstarch with water; add to veggie mixture.
Cook and stir about 1 minute until sauce is thickened.
Serve over hot rice, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked beef stew
directions: In a large bowl, combine the tomatoes, water, tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 3-quart baking dish. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 3/4 to 2 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender. Serve in bowls.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend sugar, milk and butter.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onions and sauce in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake 1 hour in 375° oven.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar about 4 minutes until fluffy.
Stir in cooled chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at medium speed on electric mixer.
After each addition and scraping bowl sides constantly, turn into pastry shell.
Chill several hours or overnight until set.
Garnish with whipped cream and chocolate curls, if desired.

title: bird seed snack
directions: Mix well and store in plastic bags or an airtight container.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, and milk. Cook to soften ball. Add vanilla and nuts. Stir until mixture is grainy and thick. Turn out immediately onto waxed paper and quickly separate nuts with fork.

title: sausage with red rice casserole
directions: Saute rice, onion and bell pepper in skillet until golden brown.
Put rice mixture in casserole.
Cover with tomatoes and mix in sausage, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german chocolate delight
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pan. Mix cake mix as directed on box and spread over pecans in pan.

title: glorified rice
directions: Beat whipping cream in small bowl until stiff; blend in sugar and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine rice, pineapple and banana.
Fold in whipping cream.
Spoon into serving dishes; garnish with cherries.
Chill before serving.

title: pat's cheese straws
directions: Beat margarine and grated cheese until fluffy.
Add cayenne pepper and salt.
Add flour 1/2 cup at a time until all is combined.
Put in cookie press or pastry bag and press out on ungreased cookie sheets.
Cook at 375° for 10 minutes or until crisp.
Store in tins.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar, coconut and pecans; melt margarine. Add to mixture along with eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients well; pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan (no need to grease pan).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
While cake is still hot, add icing.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and bake in a large buttered casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk when well blended; add the blueberries.
Bake in greased pan (muffin tin) at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: roast wild duck
directions: Place onion and apple in cavity of duck.
Place bacon slices over breast.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Place in baking pan and roast at 325° until tender, about 3 to 4 hours.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone; boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Mix soups, mushrooms, pimentos, spices and chicken.
Drain spaghetti and mix with sauce.
Top with cheese.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Stir in tuna, soup, mushrooms, peas and milk.
Pour in serving dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Stir in bananas, milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and nuts.
Chill 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Frost or glaze.

title: chicken salad sandwich roll
directions: Boil chicken in water with salt and garlic powder to taste. Cool and debone.
Grind chicken meat and eggs and green onions together very fine.
Add green olives and mayonnaise to taste.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Toast the nuts by placing on a cookie sheet in oven for 10 minutes.
Combine sugar, water, cinnamon, cloves and salt. Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes or until a candy thermometer reads 320°.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts. Stir until the mixture is cloudy.
Pour into a buttered platter using 2 forks to separate nut clusters.
Makes 1 pound.

title: cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan with shortening.
Place egg and milk in medium mixing bowl and beat until blended.
Add other ingredients.
Stir to blend and beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Pour batter into prepared baking pan.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until top of loaf springs back when you touch it with your finger.

title: a.1. sweet and sour kabobs
directions: Mix ground beef, 1/4 cup steak sauce, bread crumbs and egg; shape into 24 meatballs.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Mix remaining steak sauce with reserved juice.
Set aside.

title: cheese spread
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, flour and vinegar.
Cut up cheese and add to egg mixture.
Mix well and cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir while cooking.
Remove from heat and stir in pimentos.
Serve on crackers or on bread as sandwich.

title: pineapple ham 'n cheese on rice
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Press cooked rice into an oiled ring mold. Leave about 5 minutes.
Unmold rice while still warm and spoon cheese mixture into center.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: no bake breakfast bars
directions: Combine peanut butter, honey and brown sugar in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in cereal and fruit bits; mix well.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray
or butter the pan.
Cool 15 minutes before cutting.

title: glorified corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place approximately 2 tablespoons cooking oil in 10-inch ovenproof skillet or 8-inch or 9-inch square baking pan.
Place pan in hot oven until oil is hot.
Tilt pan to coat bottom evenly.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour mixture into hot greased pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sponge cake(small)
directions: Put yolks in a bowl.
Add warm water and beat until very light, almost filling a large bowl.
Add gradually the cup of sugar and keep beating until very creamy.
Stir in the flour and beat the egg whites to a froth.
Fold them into the sponge cake mixture.
Then add the salt, vanilla and baking powder.
Pour into ungreased tube and bake 40 or 50 minutes.
Very slowly the first 15 minutes (250°) and then increase temperature to 350°.
Turn upside down on a clean towel and cover pan with the towel so the cooling will be gradual.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Beat sugar and Miracle Whip until smooth.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in walnuts; pour into Bundt pan, greased.
Bake 55 minutes at 350° or until center comes out clean with a toothpick.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs.
Add to egg mixture the cooking oil and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Add grated zucchini and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured pans. Bake 1 hour or more at 325°.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Chop all vegetables finely and drain. Soften gelatin in cold water. Add boiling water.
Cool.
Fold in the mayonnaise and salt. Add vegetables. Chill until spreadable.
Use with crackers as spread or make sandwiches.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: chicken and tamale stuffed peppers
directions: Slice off top of each pepper, leaving stems intact.
Trim bottom of each pepper, without cutting into cavity, so that peppers will stand upright.
Remove seeds and ribs from peppers. In large saucepan, cover peppers with water.
Boil 3 minutes. Drain.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter together.
Add eggs, beaten light. Add vanilla.
Add soda, baking powder, flour and nut meats (if desired).
Mix well.
Form in roll.
Wrap in cloth and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: In large saucepan mix sugar and flour well.
Stir in milk.
Add egg yolks; mix well.
Add vanilla and butter.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix concentrated lemonade and one condensed Eagle Brand milk together.
Add 3/4 tub of Cool Whip until smooth.
Pour mixture into graham cracker pie shells.
Makes two pies.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs stiff.
Add sugar, vanilla, salt and chocolate chips.
Mix.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Put in oven and turn it off.
Go to bed.
Don't peek.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes. Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream together.
Stir in carrots. Mix squash and onion.
Mix seasoning mix and margarine together and place 1/2 of mixture in bottom of a 7 x 12-inch cooking dish. Spoon in squash and top with remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot stuffing
directions: Saute
first 5 items together.	Place stuffing in large bowl and toss with sauteed items.
Combine soups and eggs with broth; add
to stuffing.
Put in 3 1/2 quart crock-pot.
Cook on low 4 to 8 hours.

title: monkey fun crunchies(cookies)
directions: Mash the bananas. Add all the ingredients and drop by the tablespoon on a well-greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown and crispy.
Enjoy.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Brown hamburger patties.
Drain fat.
Add soup and water to hamburger.
Put into slow cooker.
(Good for Sunday dinner.
Put on before going to church - ready when you get home.)

title: mayonnaise muffin biscuits
directions: Mix together and
pour in greased muffin tins.	Bake at 420° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together till almost done, drain.
Mix with soup and sour cream.
Pour out in a casserole dish.
Combine butter and stuffing, sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix cream cheese and ranch dressing well. chill 1 hour. Remove from refrigerator and form into roll. Pour bacon bits out onto platter. Roll cream cheese log in bacon bits to coat thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator, serve with chips or crackers.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Put trimmed bread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Add grated cheese and cooked sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper (optional).
Pour over sausage.
