Refrigerate overnight. Next morning, bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mary's husband pleasin' beans
directions: Brown ground beef and season to taste; drain.
Stir in Ro-Tel, beans and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes on low heat.
Enjoy!

title: rigatoni with bacon and ricotta
directions: Cook the bacon in a skillet until crisp; drain.
Combine the Ricotta, Parmesan, parsley, salt and pepper in a serving bowl. Toss the sauce with the hot pasta, reserved cooking water and bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: garden style chicken nuggets
directions: In a medium bowl, thoroughly combine sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese, lemon juice and garlic.
Add chicken and toss until well coated.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients
together,	except cheese, and form into a loaf.
Bake in
lightly greased shallow pan at 350° for 1 hour. Slices of cheese may be placed on top of meat loaf to melt just before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine tuna, cheese, relish, catsup, salt, pepper, onion and mayonnaise.
Mix well with a fork.
Fill each bun with mixture. Line pan or roaster with foil.
Place buns in pan and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine; add to sugar and syrup. Add vanilla, eggs, pecans and chocolate chips. Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook sugar, oleo and syrup to a boil and boil 5 minutes. Remove from stove and add soda.
Mix well.
Pour over popped corn. Pour into long cake pan and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Can add peanuts if wanted.
Separate when cool. Store in plastic bags.

title: angel hair vegetable stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry vegetables in olive oil or canola oil.
If not done enough, put lid on and add 2 tablespoons water.
Steam about 2 minutes, but vegetables should be crunchy.
Cook pasta and stir in.
Sprinkle with Molly McButter butter flavor or sour cream flavor.
Stir well on plate.
A white sauce can be substituted if you prefer.

title: "detailed" pumpkin cheese roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 1 minute. Gradually add sugar, lemon juice, salt and soda.
Fold in flour and pumpkin pie mix. Spread on a cookie sheet that has been thoroughly sprayed with Pam or Mazola.
Sprinkle the nuts on top. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. (Do not overcook!)
Turn out on a kitchen towel that has been well coated with powdered sugar.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top of pumpkin bread before you roll.
Roll like a jelly roll and set aside to cool.
When cool, unroll and spread with filling. Spread filling to within 1/2-inch of edges.

title: bean soup
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper. Drain and place in crock-pot. Add other ingredients and slow cook for at least 3 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until lemon colored; add sugar and beat well.
In the meantime, melt butter; add cocoa to saucepan as the butter melts and stir until blended.
Combine flour with sugar and eggs; add cocoa and butter mixture.
Beat; add vanilla and beat.
Bake in ungreased pan 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out of brownies without batter.

title: pea salad
directions: Layer each ingredient in order given.
Cover with mayonnaise making sure to seal edges of dish.
Sprinkle generously with McCormick Salad Supreme.
Seal dish with foil.
Let stand overnight.
When ready to serve, toss together adding 1/2 pound crumbled bacon.
Use a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Might not need a whole head of lettuce.

title: pepper steak
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in skillet. Add beef and brown on all sides. Add mushrooms, green pepper, black pepper, salt, tomato paste and bouillon. Blend well.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook, covered, for 45 minutes or until beef is tender. Add Burgundy.
Heat through. If desired, thicken with cornstarch dissolved in water. Serve over rice.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes. Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese; stir until mixture is thoroughly combined.
Cool. Fold in apples, nuts, celery and Cool Whip topping.
Pour in 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken santa fe
directions: Microwave potatoes 10 minutes or until tender.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Combine 1 stick melted margarine and the graham cracker crumbs.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch and water.
Stir in milk and egg yolks.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cover and chill 4 hours. Spread Cool Whip over pie when cool.

title: ham steak on grill
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ham.
Stir thoroughly. Marinate ham in sauce for 6 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Cook on hot grill for 30 to 40 minutes, basting with sauce.

title: vermicelli with asparagus and slivered chicken
directions: Preheat the broiler or grill.
Rub chicken with 1 teaspoon mustard; broil or grill until cooked through, 4 to 5 minutes on each side.

title: jambalaya
directions: In Dutch oven, fry bacon until crisp; add chicken.
Cook until no longer pink.
Remove meat; set aside.
Saute onions, pepper, carrots, celery and garlic in hot drippings until crisp-tender. Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, broth and rice.
Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients, except okra and parsley.
Bring to a boil. Simmer, covered, for 45 to 50 minutes or until rice is cooked. Stir in okra and parsley; heat through.
Season to taste with hot sauce.

title: zucchini-pepper stir-fry
directions: Melt margarine in medium skillet over medium heat.
Add red pepper, onion and garlic; stir-fry until red pepper is crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients; stir-fry 1 minute or until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Serve immediately.

title: filled butterhorns
directions: Cut butter into flour like pie crust.
Add rest of ingredients and chill overnight.

title: black bean soup
directions: Rinse beans in a large saucepan. Combine beans and 6 cups water. Bring to a boiling state. Reduce heat.
Simmer for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Let stand 1 hour or soak beans overnight. Drain and rinse beans.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, applesauce, egg and vanilla.
Mix sifted flour, spices, raisins and nuts in separate bowl.
Add the flour mixture to the first mixture and blend well.
Turn into well-greased 11 x 3 x 3 inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Keeps well, very moist.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together meal and sugar.
Add onion, egg and milk stirring lightly.
Drop teaspoon of batter for each hush puppy into hot deep fat (360°), frying only a few at a time until golden brown; drain.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Work into this the oleo or butter.
Add sweet milk; mix well.
Roll to 1/4 inch thick.
Spread with melted oleo.
(I use the balance of the 3 tablespoons mentioned) and enough chopped apples to cover dough to 1/4 inch of edge.
Add brown sugar to taste.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll as a cinnamon roll, pinching edges to roll.
Cut into 1/2 inch slices. Place into pan as you would cinnamon rolls.
Cover with sauce. Bake at 350° until brown and apples are done.

title: zesty potatoes
directions: Wash and slice potatoes (do not peel).
Place in casserole dish 3 to 4 potatoes deep.
Add enough water to cover bottom of dish. Salt potatoes lightly.
Melt butter and drizzle over potatoes. Sprinkle Italian dressing mix over and through potatoes.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes (until potatoes are tender).
Use a whole packet of dressing mix for large casserole, or about 1/2 packet for a smaller one.

title: chili mac
directions: In large skillet brushed with oil, brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese. Simmer gently for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese and heat until melts.

title: minted fruit
directions: Pour creme de menthe over fruit 20 minutes or more before serving.
Nice to serve just before you main course.

title: roberta's flank steak
directions: Mix first five ingredients. Marinate meat overnight in sauce. Drain marinade and heat barbecue meat 5 minutes per side (for rare).
Transfer to platter. Slice thinly (as for London Broil) and pour marinade over meat.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fig preserves
directions: Bring figs and sugar to boil in heavy pot (1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon lemon rind, optional). Add Jell-O. Pour in jars; seal.

title: creamy ham and macaroni bake
directions: *Tip:
One 10.5 ounce can Green Giant cut spears asparagus, drained, can be substituted for frozen asparagus.

title: herb seasoned pork chops
directions: On waxed paper, combine bread crumbs and thyme. Dip each pork chop into egg; coat with bread crumb mixture.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oleo, cook pork chops until browned on both sides.
Remove chops. Stir in soup, milk and onion.
Heat to boiling. Return chops to skillet, turning to coat with soup mixture.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until pork is fork-tender.

title: delicious apple (fruit) dip
directions: Combine ingredients and mix with hand mixer.

title: chicken enchiladas(serves 4)
directions: Saut onion in butter; add chilies, cream cheese and chicken. Stir over low heat until well mixed. Spoon 3 tablespoons mixture onto each tortilla; roll tightly and place seam side down in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle cheese on top and then drizzle with the 2 cups of cream. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serve with taco sauce.

title: rice gratin with summer squash and red pepper
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat the oil over moderate heat.
Add onion and saute, stirring for 1 minute.
Add red pepper and saute, stirring for 2 minutes.
Add zucchini, yellow squash, garlic, salt and pepper; saute, stirring occasionally for 3 to 5 minutes or until the squash is barely tender.
In a large bowl, combine the squash mixture with rice, eggs, Cheddar cheese and basil.
Transfer to a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes. If desired, brown under broiler for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour dipping sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: barbecued trout
directions: Place trout in a single layer in a plastic bag or glass baking dish.
Combine the soy sauce, ketchup, lemon juice, oil and rosemary; pour into bag or dish.
Cover (or close bag) and let stand for 1 hour, turning once.

title: fiesta dip
directions: In mixing bowl, combine softened cream cheese and picante sauce. Beat with electric mixer at low speed until smooth. Serve with corn chips, tortilla chips or vegetables, etc. Yield: 2 cups.

title: pork and ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving 1/2 of soup for top of loaf.
Pour remaining soup on top of loaf and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake one hour or longer at 350°.

title: granny bread
directions: Mix ingredients together. Pour into a greased or nonstick 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Cream separately cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 egg, set aside.
Mix margarine, water and chocolate in saucepan and bring to boil.
Stir in flour
and
cups
sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream, soda and salt; pour	in
baking
pan, then pour in creamed mixture and
marble
through.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces. Grease and flour pan.
Bake
at
for	25
to 30 minutes.

title: bittersweet chocolate torte with apricot filling
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray two 8-inch round cake pans with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large mixer bowl, beat the eggs, sugar and vanilla until thick and tripled in volume, about 7 minutes. Sift flour, cocoa, allspice, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Quickly and gently fold the dry ingredients into the egg mixture until smooth. Divide the mixture between the 2 prepared pans.
Bake until a toothpick in the center of the cake comes out clean, about 15 minutes. Cool completely in the pans. Set on racks.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt 1 cup margarine.
Stir in 1/3 cup cocoa, coconut, pecans, eggs, sugar and flour.
Spread batter in a 15 x 10 1/2-inch pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Spread with Marshmallow Creme while hot.
Blend powdered sugar and remaining cocoa.
Add remaining margarine, milk and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Ice cake.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown meat, cook according to seasoning directions.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In skillet, cook meat, onions and peppers until done.
Drain; add chili sauce or catsup, soup and water.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover top with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 minutes or until Tater Tots are golden brown.

title: taco casserole
directions: *Bell pepper or hot peppers.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: In small saucepan, put 1/4 to 1/2 cup water.
Sprinkle gelatine over water and let set for 2 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
After gelatine has set for 2 minutes, heat until dissolved; stir constantly.
Mix with rest of water and slowly add to cream cheese mixture, beating as added. Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill.
Top with fruit before serving.
Must be refrigerated.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak dried apricots 1/2 hour and cut fine.
Mix egg, water, orange juice, flour, baking powder, baking soda and pinch of salt. Stir in apricots and nuts.
Pour in well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: mexican pie
directions: Mix oil, cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, milk and egg in a mixing bowl and set aside.
In skillet, brown sausage, beans and water; bring to boil.
Pour into 2-quart shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Spoon corn meal mixture around edge of baking dish (evenly).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done. Makes about 5 1/2 cups.

title: szechuan broccoli
directions: Combine soy sauce, rice vinegar and sugar in a small bowl; set aside.
Heat a large skillet or wok over medium heat.
Add sesame seed; cook 1 minute or until browned.
Remove seed and set aside. Add oil and next 3 ingredients to skillet.
Stir-fry 30 seconds. Add soy sauce mixture; stir well.
Cover and cook 2 minutes or until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate banana mousse
directions: Combine chocolate, 1/4 cup (60 ml) of the milk and the sugar replacement in top of double boiler.
(Chill remaining milk in freezer.)
Cook and stir over simmering water until chocolate melts.
Pour amount of hot chocolate mixture over egg yolks and beat well.
Pour egg mixture into chocolate mixture on top of double boiler.
Stir in salt.
Cook and stir over hot water until mixture thickens.
Cool completely.
Scrape cold or slightly frozen milk into mixing bowl and beat until very stiff.
Fold chocolate mixture into stiffly beaten milk.
Fold in vanilla and banana slices.
Spoon into mold, freezer tray or individual cups and freeze until firm.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: ever ready slaw
directions: Mix together.
Add cooled dressing and store in tightly covered dish in refrigerator for few hours, stirring few times. Will keep fresh and crunchy in refrigerator.

title: jam bars
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, brown sugar, oats and softened butter together until crumbly.
Press 1/2 mixture into greased 8-inch pan, then spread jam on top and put rest of mixture on top of jam.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes until brown.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Combine eggs, muffin mix, 2 cans corn, sour cream and butter. Stir with a fork and pour into 11 x 7 x 1 3/4-inch buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.

title: grandma hale's mocha fudge pudding
directions: Grease lightly one casserole dish.
Sift together flour, sugar, 3/4 cup cocoa, baking powder and the salt in a medium size bowl.
Combine the milk, margarine and vanilla and stir this mixture into the sifted dry ingredients.
Blend well and pour into casserole dish.
Mix together the brown sugar and 3 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle evenly over the batter.
Top with coffee.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: speedy mediterranean shrimp
directions: Bring zucchini, tomatoes and broth to boil and simmer 4 minutes, until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Add shrimp and olives and simmer 4 minutes until shrimp are opaque and cooked through. Remove from heat and add pepper.

title: creamy no-cook frosting
directions: Mix Crisco, butter, sugar and flour together and beat well. Scald 1/4 cup milk and add to the Crisco mixture.
Gradually add the rest of the 2/3 cup milk (cold). Beat well. Add the vanilla to the mixture. Beat until fluffy.

title: company egg casserole
directions: In large frying pan, melt margarine.
Set aside to cool. Place diced mushrooms into cooled margarine and stir until completely coated.
In large bowl, beat eggs until blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mushrooms.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Test with a knife; done when it comes out clean.
If using Egg Beaters, increase time 15 to 20 minutes.
Great for heart patients.

title: cheese apple crisp
directions: Peel and thinly slice apples.
Place in a medium bowl about 1/4 cup of sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and 1 cup cheese.
Toss well. Transfer to a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
In a medium bowl, combine remaining sugar and flour with cinnamon.
With pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and bake just long enough to melt cheese.
Serve hot.

title: chicken dijon #1
directions: Heat olive oil in saute pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add chicken and brown on both sides.
Also add garlic and green onion (don't burn garlic).
When chicken is browned, lower heat to medium and then add flour to oil in pan and mix.
(Tilt the pan to expose oil.)
This makes the roux.

title: spiedie's
directions: Mix all ingredients except meat. Add meat to sauce. Marinate overnight. Skewer and grill.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put peaches, pineapple and grapes in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, stir dry pudding mix into juice.
Pour this over fruit and stir.
Chill.
Shortly before serving, add sliced bananas.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Spoon into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Recipe can be prepared ahead.

title: american chop suey
directions: Cook and scramble ground chuck until changes color.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook very slowly for 1 hour.

title: lime pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and condensed milk together.
Add about 2/3 of the Cool Whip and then the lime juice.
Turn into the pie shell and cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: mexican grits souffle
directions: Stir grits into boiling water; add salt.
Cook 10 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently, until grits are thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Saute onion and garlic in butter; add to grits.
Stir in peppers.
Add a small amount of hot grits to egg yolks, stirring well.
Add egg yolk mixture to grits, mixing well.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into grits.
Spoon mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese specialty
directions: Cook vegetables and macaroni according to package directions. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and heat.
May sprinkle grated cheese over top, if desired.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box using 9 x 13 pan. Poke holes in cake using end of wooden spoon.
Pour evaporated milk over cake.	Pour caramel in holes, then butterscotch.
Let cool. Then top with Cool Whip and sprinkle Heath bits on top. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and spread half in pan, use half cheese and chopped pepper.
Top with other half mixture and put other half cheese on top.
Bake for 350° for 40 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie plate 2/3 full with sliced apples.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks of margarine and blend with egg, flour and sugar.
Pour mixture over apples.
Sprinkle walnuts over top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: danish pickles(green tomato spice pickles)
directions: Peel tomatoes and boiling salted water until barely tender. Drain and stick 2 to 3 whole cloves into each, depending on size. Make a syrup of the vinegar and sugar by boiling together until thickened. Pour syrup over tomatoes and let stand overnight.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: skillet goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain. Add cream cheese, soup and drained corn. Stir until warm. Place biscuits on top. Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in the blender.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into glasses.
Chill in freezer.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake about 55 minutes.
Cool on rack before slicing.

title: salmon delights
directions: Debone salmon. (Save liquid from salmon in case mixture needs to be moistened.) Put in large mixing bowl. Add salt and pepper. Then add eggs, peas, corn, carrots and onion. Combine and then add potatoes and bread crumbs. Mix well. Roll into patties and coat with flour. Drop in hot oil and fry until brown on both sides.

title: huevos rancheros(country eggs)
directions: In crepe pan, melt unsalted butter and fry eggs until done. Put eggs on a warm plate.

title: triple berry jam
directions: Mash strawberries, raspberries and blueberries to make 4 cups of pulp.
Stir in the pectin; let stand 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Put in saucepan, cook and stir over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Remove from heat; stir in Equal.
Ladle into freezer containers, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal and label.
Let stand at room temperature 4 to 6 hours.
May be stored 3 weeks in refrigerator or 6 months in freezer.
Makes about 4 cups (64 one tablespoon servings).

title: easy beef casserole
directions: Put meat in casserole with wine, consomme, onion, pepper and rosemary.
Mix together flour and bread crumbs.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours until meat is fork-tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Lightly salt and pepper pork chops.
Dip in egg and cracker crumbs and back again the egg and crumbs.
Fry in oil until coating is golden brown.
Place in baking dish and cover with cream of mushroom soup, onion soup and green onion top.
Mix these together before pouring.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood fancies
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Separate rolls into 12 pieces, then 3 layers.
Mix together crabmeat, shrimp, cheese, mayonnaise, onion, parsley flakes and curry powder.
Spoon mixture on each dough piece.
Top with water chestnuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Put into baking dish.
Cook rice.
Add milk.
Lay chicken over rice.
Put celery soup over chicken.
Put mushroom soup over chicken.
Sprinkle onion mix over chicken.
Bake at 350° in oven covered with aluminum foil to brown top.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours in oven.
Remove foil the last 15 minutes.

title: mrs. jimmy carter's strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into angel food cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients and roll out and cut.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 10 minutes.
Broil until brown.

title: pierogi shells
directions: Mash potatoes and add Velveeta.
Stuff shells with potato mixture and put in glass baking dish.
Grill onions and butter in pan, then pour over shells.
Cover and heat through at 350°.
This tastes like pierogi, only it's a quicker way.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat potatoes until fluffy.
Add other ingredients.
Beat again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with brown sugar and pecans.

title: crepes
directions: Melt 1 teaspoon butter in a small frying pan (high).
Pour 1/4 cup of batter into pan.
Spread around so batter covers the bottom of the pan.
Flip.
The crepes should be golden brown.
Fill with fresh fruit or jam and vanilla ice cream.
Roll up; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: dilled potato salad
directions: Cook and cool potatoes.
Chill.
In a bowl combine mayo, milk and lemon.
Stir in celery, onion, parsley, salt, dill weed and pepper.
Add potatoes to dressing and mix.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix together the Bisquick and brown sugar.
Then add the eggs and oil; mix well.
Then mix in chopped pecans, coconut and chocolate chips.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: layered casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Put in bottom of casserole dish. Cover with a layer of chopped onion and a layer of sliced raw potatoes.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Cover with Velveeta cheese slices.
Top with mushroom soup.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender at 350°.
Cover casserole with foil before baking.

title: blueberry krisp
directions: Butter a quart size casserole dish.
Pour can of pie filling into dish.
In a separate mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, oleo and salt.
Cut with pastry cutter or fork until mixture is crumbly (small pieces).
Add pecans to this mixture.
Sprinkle mixture over pie filling.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until crispy and brown on top.
Serve warm with whipped cream or other topping.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix Mayonnaise and slaw dressing.
Prepare broccoli, onions, cheese and bacon bits.
Coat with mayonnaise/slaw dressing.

title: quick chocolate frosting
directions: Bring to a boil after sugar dissolves; boil for 2 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and beat until ready to spread.
Frosts 2 layers or one 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: no-fat pecan pie
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients together.
Add pecans and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Decorate top of pie with pecan halves. Bake about 50 minutes at 350° in center of oven.

title: cocoa cookie candy
directions: Bring to a rapid boil and boil for 3 minutes. Remove from stove and add Minute oats, then add nuts and stir well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Chill and serve.

title: peanut butter divinity roll
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, vinegar and water. Cook on high until mixture forms soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add gradually to beaten egg white (beaten stiff).
Add marshmallow cream, salt and vanilla.
Continue beating until stiff.
Pour onto greased surface.
Roll or pat out. Spread with peanut butter. Roll as jelly roll.
Cut into 3 small rolls and chill in refrigerator.
Slice.
Instead of greased surface you can dust a pastry cloth well with powdered sugar.
Pour divinity out on it.
It makes it easier to handle.

title: mustard ring(salad)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Soak gelatine in water and dissolve over hot water.
Add dissolved gelatine and vinegar to beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients and cook over hot water, stirring until thickened and creamy*.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into ring mold and chill several hours or overnight.
Unmold and fill center with cole slaw.**

title: cheddar nut bread
directions: Combine baking mix, cheese, evaporated milk, water, nuts and egg.
Mix vigorously for 30 seconds or until blended.
Spoon into a buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.

title: denise's spaghetti and chicken casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Mix together chicken, pimento, green pepper and onion.
Add spaghetti, soup and broth.
Add salt, pepper and 1/2 of grated cheese; mix well.
Place mixture in 9 x 13-inch baking dish, top with remaining cheese.
Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Cover well.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes, uncover and bake 30 minutes more, until bubbly.

title: 24 hour salad(vegetable)
directions: Shred lettuce and place in shallow serving dish (about 4 quart size).
Top with onions, celery and water chestnuts.
Open peas and break apart.
Sprinkle peas over the salad.
Then spread mayonnaise evenly over the top.
Sprinkle with sugar, Parmesan cheese, seasoned salt and garlic powder.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator as long as 24 hours.

title: yummies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add eggs, then flour and vanilla.
Spread dough in oblong pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit (use about 2/3 cup juice).	Mix pudding in juice about 3 minutes.
Add Tang and fruit.
Cover and chill.

title: bran muffins
directions: Add soda to water and let cool.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs to creamed ingredients and stir.
Stir in buttermilk, flour and salt.
Add all-bran, raisins, nuts, dates and 40% Bran Flakes, also the water and soda, to the rest.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.
Keeps 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: pecan penuche candy
directions: Put in saucepan the brown sugar, sour cream and corn syrup. Cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Add the butter and vanilla.
Let stand without stirring until candy cools to 112°.
Add the pecans and stir until stiff enough to drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper. Let stand a few hours before removing from paper.
Store in layers with wax paper between.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix oil, grated zucchini, onion and Cheddar cheese in large bowl.
Beat eggs with wire whisk separately, then add to zucchini mixture.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in margarine.
Mix with rice.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chinese supper skillet
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender (use shortening, if necessary).
Stir to separate meat; pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat; cook 10 minutes or until rice is done.
Stir often.
Serve with additional soy.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: gumbo
directions: Saute okra in fat; add celery and onions.
Add seafood.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add parsley and serve over steamed rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Put
together in order, shortening, Sweet 'N Low, eggs, bananas, salt,
soda,
flour, nuts and baking powder.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients. Put in refrigerator until firm.

title: hot turkey casserole
directions: Mix turkey, celery, water chestnuts, mayonnaise, chicken broth and soup. Cover with stuffing mix that was tossed with melted margarine. Bake at 350° covered with foil for 25 minutes. Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Heat applesauce in pan and add baking soda while hot.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Use toothpick to test whether cake is done.

title: oat bran muffins(light recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Coat 12 muffin cups with vegetable spray or line with paper cups.
Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add next 3; mix only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in apple and cinnamon.
Fill cups almost full.
Bake 15 minutes or until browned.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Roll chicken and wrap in bacon.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 275° uncovered for 3 hours. (This can be made a day ahead.)

title: pineapple refrigerator pie
directions: Mix together the first two ingredients.
Add pineapple and stir.
Add Cool Whip and stir until well blended.
Pour into a cooled, baked pie shell.
Keep refrigerated.

title: grandma esh's coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy, then add eggs.
Add milk to coconut to fill a 1-cup measure.
Combine flour and baking powder, then add this alternately with the milk to the sugar and butter.
Mix well, then pour into 2 layer pans or 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potatoes and onions
directions: Wash potatoes, leave skins on and slice.
Slice onions into half rings.
In a 11 x 13 or larger pan greased with bacon grease, layer potatoes.
Sprinkle light with seasoning salt, then onions. Repeat until dish is full or you are out of potatoes and onions. Place pats of butter on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and cover with cheese.
Enjoy.

title: refrigidair rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in cup of warm water. Add buttermilk and yeast.
Mix real good before refrigerating overnight.
Roll out and cut like biscuits.
Fold over and butter tops.
Let stand in baking pan for 2 hours before baking until they raise.
Bake at 350°.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Let butter soften before starting so it will cream well with the sugar.
Roll the lumps out of the brown sugar with rolling pin to avoid lumps in cookies.
Add eggs and then the nuts before the flour, that you have mixed with the soda and salt.
Add vanilla in with the eggs.
Roll in two 1 1/2-inch thick rolls.
Chill and slice 1/4-inch thick and then bake at 350° until brown on top. This recipe yields about 100 cookies, so good with a cup of coffee.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together. Put in baking dish and cook at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly coat a 2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread the vegetables evenly across the bottom of the dish.
Fold the thin end of each chicken breast under the thick end so they will cook evenly.
Arrange on top of the vegetables.

title: quiche mediterranean
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute onion and eggplant in oil until tender, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, parsley and basil. Cook 5 minutes longer.
Spoon mixture into pie shell.
Mix cream, eggs, cheese and 3/4 teaspoon of salt until blended.
Pour over tomato mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in a casserole dish. Mix last 3 ingredients well and pour over layered casserole. Let stand 1 hour and enjoy.

title: crackling bread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
thoroughly and pour into greased pan. Bake
for
1 hour at 325°.
The top of bread should also be greased before baking.

title: mindy's mom's italian sausage topping
directions: Slice 1/2 green pepper and 1/4 of an onion into long strips. Place in a small skillet on medium heat with a pat of butter and 2 tablespoons of olive oil or vegetable oil. When vegetables are soft, add salt and pepper to taste. Eat over Italian sausage.

title: eclair ring
directions: Bring water and butter to boil in saucepan. Stir in flour until smooth. Stir in eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well after each addition. Stir until thick and smooth. Drop by spoonfuls on a greased pizza pan, forming a circle. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes. Do not open door. Shut off oven. Leave in oven for 20 minutes. Cool and slit ring in half. Put filling on bottom half; replace top of ring on pudding. Drizzle with chocolate frosting (melted).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with seasoning in small amount of water until squash is well done.
Drain well.
Layer squash and Cheddar cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and slightly brown.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain pears and heat just almost to a boil.
Pour over jello and set aside.
Chop pears.
Add cream cheese to jello while hot. Add pears when cool.
Refrigerate until almost jelled.
Add whipped cream and pour into mold.
Chill.

title: nut-apricot rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the yeast (yeast in warm milk goes in last.)
Mix nuts with sugar as sweet as you want. Add milk slowly and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Let dough raise for 1 hour, covered, in warm place.
Take off small piece of dough; roll it out and put in filling.
Roll up; bake 1/2 hour.
Put in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Beat up 1 egg, drop of water and pinch of sugar.
Brush on rolls right before you put back in oven.

title: hard gingerbread
directions: Hand mix ingredients and slowly add 4 to 6 cups of flour. Start with 4 to 4 1/2 cups and add enough to make a firm stiff mixture.
This is only a guide, about 5 cups may be enough, should be moist but not wet.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
In 9 x 13-inch pan (lightly greased), hand score top, length and crosswise and sprinkle sugar lightly on top before baking.
Slice 1/2-inch butter.
Great with breakfast coffee.
(This recipe has been in our family for years.)

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat, drain grease, return meat to skillet and add jar of pizza sauce.
Heat until it simmers.
Mix eggs, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley and garlic powder.

title: meat loaf with creole sauce
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients for meat loaf.
Mix and blend well to a smooth consistency.
Place meat in a greased loaf pan. Smooth top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.
Prepare sauce.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut shortening in.
Combine egg, water and vinegar. Pour liquid into flour mixture all at once.
Blend with spoon until flour is all moistened.
This is an easy crust to handle and can be re-rolled, without toughening.
Keeps in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Yields 2 double crust pies.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken.
Cut celery in large pieces.
Add salt and water to cover.
Simmer over low heat for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken from bone.
Place in lightly greased baking dish.
Drizzle butter over chicken.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Crust:
In 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine melted butter and then graham cracker crumbs.
Form into bottom of pan.

title: texas two breakfast casserole
directions: In a skillet saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add the squash, garlic, chiles, salt and pepper.
Saute till squash is crisp tender, about 5 minutes.
Add corn and stir 2 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand until cheese melts.

title: savory blade pot roast
directions: In skillet, brown meat slowly in a small amount of hot oil. Sprinkle meat with a little salt.
Combine vinegar, oil, catsup, soy sauce, Worcestershire, rosemary, garlic powder and mustard; pour over meat.
Cover tightly and simmer 2 hours or until tender. Remove meat to heated platter.
Skim excess fat from sauce; spoon sauce over meat.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crock pot fudge
directions: Place the peanuts on bottom. Then Germans chocolate, white chocolate and chocolate chips in crock pot slow cooker. Cook on low until the chocolate is melted. Stir the mixture well. Drop by tbsp. onto waxed paper. Let stand until cool. Store in an airtight container. Yield: 4 1/2 pounds.

title: pepper steak
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add beef; cook, turning frequently, until brown, about 5 minutes.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes for round steak, 5 to 8 minutes for sirloin.
Add green peppers during last 5 minutes of simmering. Blend cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce; stir into beef mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Cut each tomato into sections and place on beef mixture.
Cover; cook over low heat just until tomatoes are heated through, about 3 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: salad dressing(oil and vinegar)
directions: Shake well and refrigerate overnight.
This makes 1 pint.

title: egg, cheese and sausage strata
directions: Place cubed bread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with 3/4 of cheese and all of the sausage.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over bread, etc.
Mix lightly with a fork. Sprinkle remainder of cheese on top.
Allow to set overnight in the refrigerator.
Next day, bake uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Mix margarine and dressing.
In a large buttered baking dish, layer the 2 mixes, end with dressing on top.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: country store stir-fry teriyaki
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
Cook vegetables and beef together according to vegetable directions.
Serve on a bed of rice. Ready in minutes. Serves 2.

title: easiest grape punch
directions: Make an ice ring of the ginger ale and seedless grapes.
When ready to serve, pour sparkling white grape juice in punch bowl with ice ring.

title: cashew chicken
directions: In small bowl, toss chicken, soy sauce and garlic powder; set aside.
In 2-quart casserole, microwave oil on High for 2 minutes. Stir in chicken mixture and microwave 4 minutes or until chicken is done, stirring once.
Set aside.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients in microwave bowl. Cook 4 minutes on High; stir.
Cook 4 more minutes on High. Add vanilla and butter; stir. Cook 1 minute. Add baking soda; stir. Pour in buttered pizza pan or cookie sheet. Cool.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook chicken; set aside to cool.
Boil eggs and peel.
Mix cornbread and chicken broth.
Add all other ingredients; mix well. Pour into baking pan and refrigerate overnight.
Cook at 400° until done.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and butter, stirring well.
Sprinkle over top of casserole. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and allow to set at room temperature 1 hour.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: frozen almond cookies
directions: Roll into 3 sausages; refrigerate overnight.
Slice thin and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat yolks, then beat whites. Cream butter and sugar. Add the egg yolks and mix well. Add stiffly beaten egg whites alternately with flour. Bake in warm oven. Gradually increase the heat to about 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake on bottom shelf of oven until filling doesn't shake.
Finish on middle shelf until knife comes out clean.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries
and sugar and let stand overnight. Drain well
and
add remaining ingredients.
Let stand several hours. Good served with nut bread.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Cream shortening or applesauce with sugar and egg.
Combine flour, soda (optional cinnamon) and salt together.
Alternate milk and flour mixture together with creamed mixture.
Add vanilla. Fold in apples and chopped nuts to combined ingredients.

title: caribbean barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute.
Use to brush chicken during broiling or grilling.
Makes 1 1/2 cups or enough for 2 broilers.
